title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 8 X 8-inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Set aside to cool before frosting.

title: crock-pot steak and gravy
directions: Place steak pieces into crock-pot.
Add both soups and water. Stir; cover crock-pot and turn on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix jello, water, 7-Up and crushed pineapple.
Let partially set; then add bananas and marshmallows.
For second layer combine pineapple juice with flour, sugar and egg.
Cook until thick. Spread over first layer.
Top with Dream Whip or any whipped cream.

title: rhubarb
directions: Put rhubarb and sugar in glass bowl.
Let stand overnight. Stir mixture.
Put in saucepan and cook 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add Jello.
Let stay in refrigerator until jelled.

title: old-fashioned coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Blend margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add vinegar, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well.
Turn into pie shell. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: thelma chester's gingerbread
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with Mrs.
Parker's Sauce.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together for sauce.
Soak chicken in sauce for a at least 30 minutes. Grill chicken, basting with sauce.
Sprinkle with sesame seeds.

title: vegetable soup(makes 2 servings)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart nonstick saucepan, combine onions, broth mix and garlic.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are translucent. Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.
Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for about 10 minutes.
Add 2 cups water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium, cover and cook until vegetables are soft, about 20 minutes.
Using a slotted spoon, remove about 1/2 cup vegetables from saucepan.
Set aside. In blender, puree remaining soup.
Return puree to saucepan.
Add vegetables and heat.

title: chicken roll
directions: Add all together and roll. After roll is complete, roll it in chopped pecans. Decorate with fresh parsley.

title: famous amos cookies
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cake mix, pudding mix, chocolate bits, flour and nuts.
Drop by round tablespoon size balls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 16 minutes.

title: bollen waehen(onion flan from switzerland)
directions: Line a flan tin with short crust pastry. Cut the bacon into thin strips and fry in a saucepan in the cooking fat.
Cut the onions into long narrow pieces. Add this to the bacon and cook with the lid on until the onions are tender.
Allow to cool. Stir the flour into the cream or top of milk and add the eggs and seasoning.
Add this to the onion and bacon mixture. Spread in the flan case and bake in a moderate oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot spiced tea(also known as friendship tea mix)
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Combine 1 1/2 tablespoons of mix to a cup or mug of hot water.
Makes 50 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Crumble bacon.
Rub salad bowl with cut of garlic clove.
Wash and remove stems from spinach.
Blot spinach very dry.
Cut onion into thin slices.
Break spinach into bite-sized pieces and put into salad bowl.
Add half of onion slices and all of carrot.
Top with 3 tablespoons salad dressing.
Toss salad with 2 forks until all leaves are coated with dressing.
Sprinkle salad with remaining onion rings and crumbled bacon.
Preparation time: 20 minutes.
Serves 6.
Easy.
Serve immediately.

title: dip in the round
directions: Combine ingredients, except bread.
Cut center from bread, making a bowl.
Fill center with mixture.
Serve with bread as a dip.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding and milk until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mix over graham crackers.
Add a layer of graham crackers on top of pudding mix.
Pour other 1/2 of pudding mix.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Chill for about 2 hours.
Frost with chocolate.
Refrigerate until served.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt margarine.
Mix other ingredients and spread over margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes; cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with minced onion on top.
In another bowl mix the can of chicken soup, sour cream and chicken.
Cover the dish with aluminum foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake another 45 minutes.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Make a syrup of the boiling water, sugar and salt.
Add puree. Place bread cubes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture over cubes.
Let stand a while to thoroughly mix.
Melt butter and pour on top of pudding.
Bake for 50 minutes at 370°, uncovered.
Even tastes better when reheated as leftovers.

title: health food brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; mix wet ingredients.
Combine, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350° in greased casserole.
Buttered crumbs or potato chips may be added if desired to top.
This makes a very generous casserole.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, molasses and egg; add remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls; roll in additional sugar. Place balls on cookie sheet, allowing room to flatten as they bake.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Yield:
4 dozen cookies.

title: peach pie
directions: Cut peaches in half; remove the stone and slice fairly thick. Arrange peaches in pie shell.
Melt the butter and beat the egg. Mix the flour and sugar with the egg and butter and pour over the peaches.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: almond rock macaroon pudding(heritage)
directions: Beat together egg yolks and sugar.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon gelatin in 1/4 cup milk and add to eggs and sugar.
To this add remaining hot milk slowly; heat in a double boiler until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat in 3 egg whites until stiff.
Pour custard mixture over beaten egg whites.
Flavor with 1/4 cup sherry and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Crumble almond macaroon cookies into a round mold and spoon mixture over them.
Let congeal.

title: pan-fried fish
directions: Salt and pepper the fish and dredge them in cornmeal or a cornmeal-flour mixture.
Heat the cooking oil until hot.
Place fish in the pan and turn the heat down.
Brown the fish and prevent them from sticking to the pan with a spatula (takes about 8 to 10 minutes on each side; do not overcook).
When the fish are done, remove them and add the butter or margarine to the skillet. Squeeze lemon juice into the fat, stir and sprinkle this over the fish before serving.

title: party mix
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in a blender.
Pour mixture over remaining ingredients.
Use a large roaster pan (an electric roaster is ideal).
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir from bottom every 15 minutes.
When cool, store in airtight cans.
It keeps for months.

title: sugared donuts
directions: Cut each biscuit into thirds.
Roll each into a ball and place on skewers 1/2 inch apart.
Bake over hot coals, turning constantly until browned.
Drop into butter and roll in mixed sugar and cinnamon.

title: cinnamon loaf
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar in bowl until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, soda, salt and baking powder alternately with buttermilk, mixing well after each addition.
Combine 1/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and butter. Put
mixture into 2 loaf pans**. Mix
sugar and butter. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Have oven on warm temperature.
Butter 2 cookie sheets well and place in warm oven until ready to be used.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Mix the potatoes with the milk to make creamy mixture.
Roll potato mixture around each marshmallow to make balls.
Roll each ball in the crushed corn flakes and let stand 30 minutes to set. Fry in deep fat.
Serve at once.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Beat egg until light; add milk.
Drain kidney beans.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Turn into oiled baking dish.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vidalia onions
directions: In a 10-inch covered skillet, cook the onions in butter, stirring occasionally. Add sherry, sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 or 3 minutes. Turn onto serving dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: In a bowl mix well the mayo, sugar, Parmesan, vinegar, basil and salt.
Pour dressing over mixture of broccoli and cauliflower. Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: easy turkey pot pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place one pie crust in pie plate and pour ingredients inside.
Cover pie with remaining pie
crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey burritos(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart saucepan, stir tomato juice, cornstarch and 1/2 cup water until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring, until mixture boils and thickens slightly. Boil 1 minute.
Stir in salsa.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish; set aside.

title: pineapple nut pie
directions: Slowly stir lemon juice into Eagle Brand milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple (well drained) and nuts. Pour into prepared graham cracker crust and chill overnight.

title: vegetable-beef casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish the ground beef on bottom, next green beans (diced).
Spread cream of chicken soup, then vegetable mixture, next sprinkle over Cheddar cheese.

title: breaded ranch chicken
directions: In a shallow pan, combine corn flakes, dressing mix and parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in butter, then roll in corn flake mixture to coat.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter biscuits; roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place into buttered Bundt pan.
Melt butter, brown sugar and water; boil for 2 minutes and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat, fry diced bacon together with the minced onion until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Add shredded cabbage and salt and cook mixture, stirring occasionally with slotted spoon, until cabbage is tender, about 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; combine next 3 ingredients to make a dressing.
Pour dressing over first mixture and let set overnight (minimum 4 hours).
Add crumbled bacon just before serving time.

title: big bird's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mash bananas.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: mary lou's cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Alternately pour into greased Bundt pan.
Take a knife and swirl.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Heat to boiling.
Add large box of orange jello.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups water.
Refrigerate until it starts to set.
Add shredded cheese, nuts and Cool Whip.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from broth, reserving broth.
Cool and debone.
In skillet, saute about 1/4 cup onion in oil or broth until tender.
Add tomatoes.
Stir and add chicken.
Cook until somewhat dry.
Salt to taste.
Soften tortillas in oil or broth and stack.
Put about 2 tablespoons chicken filling into each tortilla with remaining uncooked chopped onion and some grated cheese.
Roll into about a 1 to 1 1/2-inch roll.
Place in baking pan.
Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour.
Add 2 cups reserved chicken broth and stir until thick.
Stir in sour cream and green pepper, if desired.
Pour sauce over enchiladas.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Top with more cheese and onion.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: dried beef sandwich spread
directions: Mix together.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: roasted pork loin
directions: Place pork loin in a pan with approximately 1 to 1 1/2 inches of water.
Top with onion soup mix or spices.
Cover tightly with tinfoil and place in oven for at least 5 hours (no peeking) in 300 to 325° oven (from 11 a.m. to 5 p.m.).
No fuss, cooks all day.

title: salsa creamy dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips or raw veggies.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll crescents onto a cookie sheet with sides and pinch seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, milk and dressing mix and spread on cool crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.
(Recipe is very easy to half.)

title: cuban water bread
directions: Dissolve yeast, salt and sugar with some of the water.
With wooden spoon, beat flour into rest of water until you have a batter.
Pour in yeast mixture and mix.
Add flour until right consistency.
Knead.
Cover bowl with a damp cloth (after putting mixture into bowl).
Let rise.
Punch down.
Divide into 2 round loaves.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle loaves with cornmeal.
Let rise 5 minutes.
Cut a cross on top with sharp knife.
Put pan in cold oven with cake
pan of boiling water on bottom of oven.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla until very stiff.
Fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apricot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake for 1 hour.
Check at 45 minutes.
After cake is done, while warm, ice with 2 cups sugar and juice from 1 lemon. Let icing drizzle down sides of cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixer, beat eggs, sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Grease and flour 2 regular loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: cabbage roll-ups with beef
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over cabbage leaves to cover; allow to stand 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine beef, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, corn, onion, salt and pepper just until blended.
Remove cabbage leaves from water.
Place about 2/3 cup meat mixture in each leaf; fold in sides and roll lengthwise. Fasten with wooden picks.

title: rabbit stew with apricots
directions: Dredge rabbit in flour, salt and pepper mixture.
Heat oil in skillet on medium-high.
Add rabbit and cook about 8 minutes, turning until browned.
Transfer to Dutch oven.
Add milk, juniper berries and bouillon cube.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 40 minutes, turning rabbit occasionally during cooking.

title: toasted italian biscottis
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a
time, until light and creamy.
Fold in flavors and milk. Then fold in the dry ingredients (flour, salt and baking powder).
Fold in cut up cherries and nuts.
Bake in a thick jelly roll pan (greased and floured), 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in 3 long lines and then in pieces 1-inch across.
Lay each piece in pan again and toast in oven until light tan.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Quickly bring pea beans to boil, then let soak 1 hour.
Then cook until skins burst.
Drain, but keep water.
Cut salt pork into two pieces.
Put 1 piece on bottom of pot and add beans.
Mix salt, molasses, dry mustard and brown sugar and pour over beans.
Add enough bean water to cover.
Place salt pork on top of beans, rind side up.
Bake 5 to 7 hours at 250°.
Uncover last 1/2 hour. Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli carrot vinaigrette
directions: Cook broccoli pieces in salted boiling water until barely tender.
Cook carrots to similar degree of doneness and drain; cool.
Mix all other ingredients in jar; shake vigorously to blend.
Place drained vegetables in low dish.
Pour dressing over them.
Chill for several hours.
May serve with chopped hard-boiled eggs or capers as garnish.

title: mama brig's famous cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° until done.
For a moister dressing, use more eggs or applesauce.

title: chicken pot pie(fast and easy)
directions: Tip:
Roast a whole chicken and make Pot Pie with the leftovers.

title: baked clam casserole
directions: Pour milk over crackers; let stand until milk is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender, but not browned.
Add to cracker mixture.
Add clams with liquid, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste and eggs; mix well.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: english toffee
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in saucepan and cook until brown, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in buttered pan.
Lay Hershey bars across top of hot mass and spread gently as chocolate melts.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: plain but fancy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients into a 1 1/2-quart ovenware dish (8 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch square is perfect).
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Very tasty.
One recipe makes 8 scant servings.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Prepare pie shell and set aside.
Peel, core and cube about 2 apples to measure 2 cups.
Set aside.
Sift sugar, flour and salt. Stir in egg; blend until smooth.
Add vanilla and sour cream and stir in gently.
Fold in apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Prepare Streusel Topping and spring over pie to oven for 10 minutes longer.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Cook all ingredients until cabbage and celery are tender. Add chunks of cooked chicken for a variation.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix well, bring to a rolling boil.
Pack in hot jars and seal. Makes 9 quarts.

title: st. john's couples club chiliwestboro, missouri
directions: Brown the hamburger meat and onions then add the other ingredients.

title: bruss spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon in large frying pan.
Drain grease, leaving a little grease in the pan.
Fry onion and bell pepper in pan along with bacon, but keep in separate piles.
After onion and pepper are tender, stir together with tomato soup and one can of water. Simmer.
Cook spaghetti in a pan of water as usual.
Drain.
Mix the spaghetti and the sauce together and simmer until thick.

title: barbecue marinade
directions: In small saucepan, heat oil; add onion and saute until softened.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Use as a marinade with poultry.

title: grandama's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar in bowl; add salt.
Alternate flour and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add flavorings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-mushroom scallop
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Cut into 2-inch pieces.
Melt butter over low heat in a saucepan.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Spread broccoli in 1-quart casserole.
Pour mushroom sauce over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until tender and golden brown.

title: baked fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit and reserve juice.
Use 1 cup of juice and add brown sugar and curry powder.
Heat with butter until it melts. Pour over fruit and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together, then add chopped walnuts. Roll into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden color on top (place cookie sheet in middle of oven).
Cool thoroughly, then roll into confectioners sugar.
Enjoy.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°; grease muffin tins.
Beat in large bowl the egg; stir in milk and oil and stir in remaining ingredients (except chocolate chips).
Stir until flour is moistened; fold in chocolate chips.
Fill cups 3/4 full.
Bake until brown, 20 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Prepare jello with directions on box.
Stir in cooked rice and pineapple.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter candy cake
directions: Combine water and oats.
Cool to room temperature.
Set aside. Cream together oleo, both sugars and vanilla.
Beat in eggs. Blend in oatmeal mixture.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Chop Reese's candy over top of cake.
Do not stir.
Bake it at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until red is gone from meat.
Pour off grease, then place beef in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Place cheese slices on top of beef.
In small bowl, mix mushroom soup, corn (drained) and 1/2 cup water.
Stir, then pour this mixture over beef and cheese.
Next, arrange Tater Tots on top of mixture. Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly and Tater Tots are browned nicely.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in hot oil.
Add garlic and cook until yellow.
Add soy sauce, salt and 1/4 cup water; cook 45 minutes.
(Add more water, if necessary.)
Add vegetables; cook 10 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate chips in milk.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla, then walnuts. Pour into prepared pan and spread evenly.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: weight watchers fruit salad
directions: Mix yogurt, salad dressing and pudding until creamy.
Add fruits.
Stir in carton Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: pot-roasted pork
directions: Trim excess fat from roast. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Place sliced onion in crockpot, add bay leaf, soy sauce and water. Cover and cook on low 8-10 hours.

title: pot roast
directions: Trim fat from meat. In Dutch oven, brown meat on all sides in hot oil. Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper. Cut up any large pieces of dried fruit.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter on top of stove.
Mix in box of powdered sugar.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and pour over top of mixture.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: green goddess(makes about 4 cups)
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix until smooth.
Let stand for 1 hour for flavors to blend.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix crackers, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1 stick margarine. Press down in bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix 2 cups powdered sugar, 2 egg whites and 1 stick margarine (softened). Beat 10 minutes with mixer.
Pour over first layer of mixture.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Make into cakes and fry.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together (including juice from oranges). Mix for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cake will be kind of soft set.

title: chili
directions: In large frying pan, brown hamburger; drain off all liquid. Dust hamburger with garlic powder (petty fair dusting).
Dust hamburger with chili powder (pretty fair dusting).
Sprinkle on dash of basil, then stir hamburger to mix seasonings well.
Place in 4 or 5-quart pot.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with wax paper.
Butter pan and wax paper.
Mix pumpkin, evaporated milk, sugar, eggs and cinnamon together and pour into pan.
Pour 1 box cake mix over pumpkin.
Mix and sprinkle with nuts over cake mix. Spoon melted butter over nuts evenly.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Check to see if knife comes out clean.
Cool slightly. Turn over and pull off wax paper after cooled.

title: mexican grubb
directions: Cook beef with onion; drain fat. Grease baking dish (it will stick otherwise). Cover dish with Doritos chips (be generous; use small pack). Pour mixture over chips. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°. Remove from oven. Add grated Cheddar cheese. Return to oven and bake for 5 more minutes. Serve with salad and sour cream.

title: marsala chicken
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Add chopped onions and fry until golden brown, then add all the spices.
Fry for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and fry to form a paste.
(You may have to add 1/4 cup water.)
Now add the chicken and yogurt.
Cover pan.
After 2 minutes, lower heat to medium and cook until chicken is very tender.
Serve with pita bread, tortillas or rice.

title: very flaky pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Mix liquids together and add to flour.

title: walnut chocolate chip crispies
directions: Melt half of the chocolate chips over hot (not boiling) water. In a separate mixing bowl, beat together the butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.

title: brickle blonde brownies
directions: Cream butter with both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in Bits 'O Brickle and other remaining ingredients if used.
Spread evenly in well-greased 9 x 12-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Frost with white or chocolate butter frosting.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add last 3 ingredients and pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet-hot spiced pecans
directions: In a bowl, mix first 6 ingredients. Whisk in egg white and vegetable oil. Stir in pecan halves. Spread nuts in a single layer in an oiled nonstick 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Bake in a 300° regular or convection oven, stirring occasionally, until nuts are crisp and lightly browned, 20 to 25 minutes. Let cool about 5 minutes, then use a wide spatula to loosen nuts from pan; cool completely. Serve or store airtight at room temperature up to 2 weeks. Makes about 2 cups.

title: marinated garden salad
directions: Quarter large potatoes; halve smaller ones.
Cut beans in half (about 2 cups).
In a 4 1/2 quart Dutch oven, cook potatoes, beans and carrots in lightly salted boiling water for 15 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: You will need a 9-inch pie plate.

title: white punch
directions: Freeze solid; take out 1 hour before serving.
Mix with Sprite to make a slush.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: punch
directions: Let sherbet soften, then add 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Use broth and follow directions on Lipton package when rice is done.
Take chicken off bone and cut into bite size pieces; add to rice.
Grate cheese into rice and chicken.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: pineapple cheesecake with pie crust
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Mix in pineapple.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Freeze about 2 hours or until firm in freezer. Remove 10 minutes before serving.
Serve with blueberry sauce.

title: glazed cornish hens
directions: Put the steak in the pot and hack away at it with a fork or something to open it up for the marinade.
Pour the rest of your beer over the steak; open another.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ice cream.
Let chill. Before serving, stir in vanilla ice cream.

title: baked chicken in mushroom sauce
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally.

title: saucepan fudge brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt butter or margarine and unsweetened chocolate.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 16.

title: crab roll-ups
directions: Mix butter and cheese and melt on low heat.
Add crabmeat and stir.
Roll 4 pieces of bread flat.
Spread warm crab mixture on bread (not too thick); roll and put on cookie sheet and freeze. When set, cut each roll into 3 or 4 pieces.
Dip into melted butter and broil on each side.

title: english butter toffee
directions: Butter a 10 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Combine sugar, butter, water and salt in heavy saucepan.
Place over medium-high heat and bring to boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Combine boiling, shaking pan occasionally, until temperature reaches 305°. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour onto baking sheet and let run into 10 x 10-inch square pan.
Cool until hardened.
Melt 3 ounces of each chocolate together.
Spread onto top of toffee and press in half the nuts.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Using spatula, carefully turn toffee over.
Repeat coating with remaining chocolate and nuts.
When firm, break into pieces.

title: crab ball
directions: Saute butter and onion.
Let cool.
Mix with cream cheese, lemon juice and crab meat.
Form into a ball with your hands and refrigerate overnight.
Pour seafood sauce on top just before serving.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: kid's pizza
directions: Spread "Pizza Quick" on English muffin halves.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top and/or other toppings.
Broil on cookie sheet until cheese is cooked.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease Bundt pan.
(I use Pam.) Sprinkle pan with sugar.
Pour into pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Fry butter, rice and mushrooms until rice is brown.
Put in casserole dish.
Add beef consomme and onion soup.
Stir well. Cook, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Then remove cover and cook 20 more minutes.

title: chicken swiss
directions: Lightly coat casserole dish with margarine.
Place chicken in dish. Lay cheese slice on each chicken breast.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add chicken and onion.
Cook about 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soup, milk and pimentos.
Cover and simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve over waffles or toast.

title: egg bread
directions: Mix milk, water, cooking oil, soda and salt together.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add corn meal (enough to make mixture medium stiff).
Brush top with oil or butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
I use my iron skillet.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl and cut until well mixed. Spread evenly into a 13 x 9-inch pan or larger. Press firmly.

title: dad's door county chili - version #2
directions: Brown ground beef. Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly for 2 hours or in crock-pot. Add brown stock as needed for moisture.

title: "philly" sauce superb
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add milk and cream cheese.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add mushrooms and parsley.
Heat through.
Makes a great base for chicken or beef stroganoff.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, peanut butter and add dry ingredients and shape into balls.
Press with fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 7 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: barbecued franks and beans
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup syrup.
Saute green pepper in margarine.
Add pineapple, syrup, franks, beans and barbecue sauce.
Heat thoroughly.

title: soup
directions: Mix all together.
Put on top of stove and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour tuna mixture into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except the raw vegies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: batter pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder; add to sugar mixture with milk.
Pour into baking dish. Add fruit and dot with oleo.
Bake at 375°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, stick of butter and egg.
Pour in greased pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar; pour over cake and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese with butter.
Add flour, salt and paprika.
Mix well.
Dry olives.
Wrap a spoonful of dough around each olive and seal well.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
You can freeze unbaked cheese puffs on a cookie sheet, then store them in the freezer in a plastic bag.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Crush crackers, melt butter, and mix together. Drain veg-all, mix with onions, mayonnaise, and grated cheese. Turn into greased casserole dish. Top with crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 min.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients and work in the shortening and cheese.
Add the milk.
When well mixed, toss the dough on a floured board and pat to 1/2-inch in thickness.
Shape into rounds with a biscuit cutter.
Place in an oiled baking pan.
Brush with milk and bake in a very hot oven (450°) from 12 to 15 minutes.

title: hattie's soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine wet ingredients. Add flour until soft dough. Use icing sugar to roll out dough.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut 6 eggs in half lengthwise; gently remove yolks. Coarsely chop remaining egg. Place yolks, chopped egg, mayonnaise and mustards in a self-sealing plastic bag. Seal bag. Gently squeeze the bag to combine the ingredients. Season with salt and pepper. Snip one corner of bag and squeeze bag, pushing egg yolk mixture through hole into egg white halves. Top with parsley or paprika.

title: smoked sausage goulash
directions: Cut sausage into chunks.
Combine with rice, soup, water and butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in peas and mushrooms (both are drained).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Do not stir in cheese.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fireside chat coffee
directions: I use light and decaffeinated products.

title: watergate salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into large mixing bowl; add pudding mix and stir well.
Add all other ingredients and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Cool in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.

title: potato salad
directions: Hard-boil the eggs.
Put in pan of cold water.
Bring to a boil.
Put lid on pan and turn off heat.
Allow pan to set on the burner at least 1/2 hour.
Cook the potatoes at the same time. Cook until tender all the way through. Drain and let cool. Don't mix with dressing until completely cool!

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chilies and taco seasoning. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Place 1/4 to 1/2 cup mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan or glass baking dish. Place a layer of tortillas on top of meat, then add more meat mixture, then cheese. Layer tortillas 3 times with meat and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese is bubbly. Top with lettuce, tomato and salsa.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (not until brown).

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix well.
Roll out thin.
Cut into 2 x 3-inch rectangles. Drop into hot fat and brown each side.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla together, then pour over top of cake batter.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: krisp sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add vanilla and eggs.
Combine flour and baking powder and salt; add to ingredients along with milk.
Refrigerate dough.
Drop on cookie sheets and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening in saucepan.
Heat until bubbles appear around the edge and shortening is melted. Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large mixing bowl. Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add lukewarm milk mixture.
Add 6 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead for 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.
Put into greased bowl.
Turn over with greased side up.
Cover with damp towel.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Grease and flour 1-quart pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° until firm.
Serve with creamed peas and French fries.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Pour dressing over carrots in large nonstick skillet; stir to coat.
Cover and cook on medium heat 20 minutes, stir frequently. Just before serving add almonds and parsley.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer.

title: wine camembert cheese ball
directions: Place Camembert in small bowl and cover with wine.
Cover; leave overnight.
Next day, drain off wine; chop Camembert roughly.
Put into small bowl.
Add softened butter and Tabasco and beat on medium speed until smooth and well blended. Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes.
Shape cheese into original shape of Camembert.
Roll top and sides in almonds, patting on firmly. Refrigerate until firm.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Melt 2/3 of the margarine in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Empty in hash browns; sprinkle onion on top.
Sprinkle on the shredded cheese.
Mix the sour cream, soup, salt and pepper; spread on top of cheese.
Melt remaining margarine; toss cornflakes in it. Cover the casserole with this mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: molded orange health salad
directions: Sprinkle jello into cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let stand several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Unmold.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour over hot cake. Prepare pudding according to package. Spread over cooled cake. Combine pecans, coconut and Cool Whip and spread over cake.

title: savory oyster crackers
directions: Variation:
Substitute 3/4 cup butter flavored popcorn oil for 1 cup oil and 1/2 teaspoon white pepper for lemon pepper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Rinse canned corn.
Mix corn with eggs and milk (using an electric mixer on high speed).
Add the rest of the ingredients. Put in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Stir from the bottom of the pan every 10 minutes for the first 1/2 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine oil and sugar; mix well.
Add 1/2 the dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts, carrots and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients that remain and eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake about 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Combine jello and boiling water.
Combine with lemon and sugar and allow to almost jell; then whip.
Partially freeze Carnation milk, then whip until stiff.
Combine with lemon mixture. Pour in large Pyrex dish over crust of oleo and vanilla wafers (save some to sprinkle on top).
Refrigerate.
Serves 16 to 18.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, eggs and vinegar.
Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Stir together and put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with wax paper; grease paper.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and beat well, then add carrots and walnuts, coconut and pineapple.
Bake for 1 hour on middle rack.
Top with Alma's Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: taco pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put pizza crust on pan or baking sheet. Mix tomato sauce and Mexican seasoning.
Spread over crust.
Dot with beef.
Sprinkle with chili pepper and cheese.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to
25 minutes or until meat is cooked and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomato and corn chips.
Serves 4.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Cover with crumbs or potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: okra seafood gumbo
directions: In large frying pan fry okra, turning often until no longer sticky.
Remove.
Brown ham and other seasoning.
Add okra, shrimp and crabs, mixing well.
Add about 2 quarts water and cook slowly, about 1 hour.
Add water according to thickness desired.
Add oysters and crabmeat (if canned) last.
Serve over rice.

title: angels on horseback
directions: Marinate oysters in wine and soy sauce.
Let stand at least 30 minutes.
Drain.
Cut bacon 1/2 crosswide.
Wrap each half slice around one oyster securing in place with a toothpick.
Broil 4-inches from heat 2 to 3 minutes.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Sift and stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on floured surface.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake until golden, 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Be careful not to overbake. Yields 4 dozen.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain fruit; bring 1 1/2 cups liquid to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in liquid.
Add sherbet and fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix yogurt, mayonnaise, mustard, salt and sugar in medium bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except raw vegetables. Serve with vegetables or crackers or spoon into hollowed-out loaf of bread and serve with bite size pieces of bread.
Makes about 3 1/4 cups of dip.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 3 teaspoons per 6 ounce cup of hot water.

title: mexican chiquito punch
directions: To make a whole room smell fresher, mix some vinegar, a few cloves and a little cinnamon in small jars.
Put the jars in the microwave for a minute, then place where needed.
This mix seems to absorb odors, rather than just mask them.

title: matrimonial cake
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water until dates are mushed up.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread 3/4 of it in pan; put date mixture in, then sprinkle remains of rolled oats mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: sour cream blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add gradually to the egg mixture, alternating with the sour cream and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla and cardamon.
Fold in 1 cup blueberries.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a blender, crush cookies fine and pour in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix milk and vanilla pudding together in a large bowl and add Cool Whip.
In a small bowl, mix together cream cheese and margarine.
Add to the pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
In a large ice cream bucket, place a layer of cookies, then a layer of pudding etc.
Alternate layers, ending with cookies on top.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except butter and stuffing.
Mix melted butter and stuffing.
Place 3/4 on bottom of casserole dish and 1/4 on top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: christmas lizzies
directions: Sift flour, spices and soda together.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs, blending thoroughly.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with brandy.
Dust pecans, raisins and fruit with flour.
Add to batter.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes in 275° oven.
Makes about 10 dozen and will keep for weeks (if you hide them) in airtight container or Ziploc bags.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes whole until half done.
Cool; grate potatoes. Layer potatoes, salt and butter in casserole dish.
Pour whipping cream over potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat shortening, sugar replacement and eggs until lemon-colored.
Add water, flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt, beating well.
Stir in pecans and carrots.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Blend together well.
Add peaches and juice.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake in oven at 325° until golden brown crust appears.
Serve warm alone or over ice cream.
Other fruits can be substituted.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook the onion, green pepper, celery and mushrooms in the 3/4 stick margarine until tender.
Mix pimento, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, hot sauce, Worcestershire, canned milk and lemon juice, then add to other ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Crumble saltines on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line pan with whole crackers, not crumbled.
Pour layer of pudding mixture over crackers.
Make 3 layers of crackers and pudding.
Top the last layer of pudding with whole graham crackers, covering all of the pudding.
If needed, break crackers to cover totally.
Spread frosting on the top.
Let set 24 hours in the refrigerator.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Pour peaches into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over peaches.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix and then add coconut and pecans on top.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: easter cheese
directions: Pour milk into saucepan and bring to a boil. Beat eggs slightly and gradually add to the milk.
Cook over low heat for about 7 minutes. Add pepper and salt. Stir constantly so mixture will
not scorch.
Pour mixture into a linen towel.
Squeeze and tie securely.
Hang and let drain for 2 hours. Cover with wet napkin and place in refrigerator.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and bake.
Cool cake and cut layers in half.
Mix French vanilla pudding and drained pineapple together and then fold in Cool Whip.
Frost cake and chill until served.

title: coconut pie deluxe
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in double boiler; add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Add 3/4 cup of coconut.
Cook over rapidly boiling water 15 minutes, stirring.
Mix small amount of mixture with egg yolks, return to double boiler and cook two minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cool. Turn into a cooled pie shell.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup coconut.

title: no peek beef tips
directions: Layer in a 2-quart casserole in order given.
Cover and bake 3 hours in a 300° oven.
(Do not peek.)
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Drain liquid from tomatoes and chilies.
Melt cheese in microwave.
Combine first 3 ingredients. Serve immediately or in chafing dish as it will cool quickly.

title: easy popcorn snack
directions: Mix butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add popcorn and peanuts. Put in large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar,
white
sugar,
eggs,
creamy peanut butter and margarine or Crisco well.
Add flour, soda, vanilla and salt. Drop by
spoonfuls	on
cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Simmer the raisins in the water for a few minutes.
Save 1/2 cup liquid.
Combine all the dry ingredients as listed.
Add the raisin and water mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and cooking oil.
Add eggs, vanilla and burnt sugar flavoring to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Work oatmeal, potato chips and walnuts into cookie mixture.

title: frankfurter skillet dinner
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, then remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 35 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook until candy dissolves.
Add butter or margarine.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and stir only to moisten.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut 6 squares.
Place apples.
Fill with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Fold dough around apple.
Pour syrup over all.
Bake 35 minutes in a 375° oven.
Baste a couple of times.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 12-inch casserole and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Very moist corn bread.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until tender, but firm. Let cool. Slice potatoes in small chunks, mince small onion and half pepper in one bowl. In another bowl, pour jar of mayonnaise, mix in 1/4 cup of Crisco oil and 1/4 cup of cider vinegar.
Should be thin and a little runny.
Add potatoes, onion and peppers. Sprinkle with paprika and chill.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Line bottom and sides of oval or oblong casserole dish with wafers.
Slice 1 1/2 bananas over wafers.
Add second layer of wafers.
Slice other 1 1/2 bananas over wafers.
Set aside. Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Stir in 1/2 container of Cool Whip into the pudding.
Mix well.
Pour mixture on top of bananas and wafers.
Refrigerate.
May top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: chocolate gooey bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in a jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) in oven until melted.
Sprinkle and pat cake mix (dry) over margarine.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chocolate chips and cereal.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk evenly over the top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cereal is golden brown.
While bars are warm, run knife around sides of pan to loosen edges.
Cool 2 hours.
Cut into 2 1/4 x 1 1/4-inch bars.
Makes approximately 48 bars.

title: healthy macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix drained macaroni with Cheddar cheese and milk.
Heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Spray skillet with cooking spray. Cook garlic, peppers and onion for 5 minutes.
Mix with macaroni and cheese; add tomatoes, pepper and cottage cheese and mix well. Coat 2-quart ceramic dish with cooking spray and spoon mixture into dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake 40 minutes (20 minutes covered and 20 minutes uncovered) or until preferred consistency and brown on top.

title: sausage dip
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; drain.
Melt Velveeta cheese in microwave.
Add cheese, sour cream and chiles to sausage.
Serve in chafing dish or crock-pot to keep warm.

title: wacky cake
directions: Heap all dry ingredients in 8-inch biscuit pan.
Do not grease or flour.
Add the water, cooking oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix (stir well); scrape sides.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° just as is. Do not double recipe.

title: slush
directions: Boil 7 cups water and sugar; let cool.
Boil tea and 2 cups water and steep tea bags.
Combine all the ingredients.
Freeze, stirring occasionally.
Fill glass 2/3 full.
Fill remainder of glass with 7-Up or other mixer.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Butter cake pan.
Put enough marshmallows in to cover bottom of cake pan.
Pour rhubarb over marshmallows.
Pour the sugar over the rhubarb.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over rhubarb. Bake at 350°.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix yolks and Cool Whip until soft and spreadable.
Pull apart and crumble cake.
Put Butterfinger bars in a Ziploc bag and crush. Layer in order:
cake and Cool Whip mixture, then spread Butterfinger crumbs.
Repeat layers (normally 2 layers). Refrigerate.

title: mary jezek's jumbo cornburger
directions: Combine beef with next 5 ingredients and spread half of mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients except tomato and cheese.
Spoon over meat.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Last 5 minutes, arrange tomato on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Let melt slightly.

title: pecan-chicken salad
directions: In a medium bowl mix the chicken, rice, pecans, onion and celery.
In a small bowl whisk the mayonnaise, lemon juice, pepper, thyme and basil.
Add the dressing to the chicken mixture and mix well.
Serve on lettuce and garnish with the parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry meat with onion and spices.
Drain.
Add only enough tomato sauce to moisten.
Grease 2 cookie sheets (and hands). Spread dough on sheets.
Layer meat mix and both cheeses.
Roll and pinch ends (or use toothpicks).

title: cranberry delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until slightly thickened. Combine other ingredients and fold into jello.
Chill and set.

title: au gratin pineapple casserole
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cheese and pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over the pineapple. Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with cracker crumbs.

title: prize nut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add flour and mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add.
Chop nuts and add to mix.
Bake in a loaf pan for 3/4 hour at moderate heat.

title: zucchini crab cakes
directions: Grate zucchini.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Fry in hot oil.
Tastes like crab.

title: husband's delight casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions in bowl.
Brown onions in butter.
Add tomato sauce, sugar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of noodles, beef mixture, sour cream, cream cheese and onions.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple oatmeal bars
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients, then cut in shortening until crumbly.
Spread half of mixture into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Arrange apple slices over crumb mixture.
Dot with the 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of sugar and some cinnamon over apples.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: eunice's lemon chess pies
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add margarine (room temperature) and sugar. Cream well.
Add flavor, vinegar and salt.
Cook 10 minutes at 300°, then raise to 350°.
Yield: 2 pies.

title: pecan loaf
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla together.
Add pecans.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stay crisp salad
directions: Mix shredded cabbage and carrots, green pepper and onion; sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Pour 2 cups sugar on chopped cranberries and let set for 2 hours.
Mix up jello as it says on box.
When set, pour into cranberries.
Add the rest of the ingredients and chill.

title: dirt cups
directions: In large bowl, combine pudding and milk.
Add whipped topping and 1/2 of the crushed cookies.
Divide rest of the cookies in 8 to 10 cups.
Fill 1/2 full with pudding.
Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Add gummy worms.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Heat water just to boiling in saucepan over medium-high heat. Pour the boiling water into large mixing bowl.
Add frosting mix, corn syrup and vanilla.

title: kraut relish
directions: Combine
sugar, vinegar and salt in saucepan.
Let come to
a boil;
remove
from heat and cool.
Combine kraut, bell pepper, onion,
jalapeno
pepper and pimientos.
Pour vinegar mixture over kraut mixture.
Refrigerate in a tight container. Will keep good for several weeks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and sugar into boiling water.
Set aside to cool. Grind cranberries and add all other ingredients.
Fold this mixture into the jello.
Refrigerate to set.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Put all ingredients in a bowl and beat by hand.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
When cooled, ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and pour into a 9 inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian macadamia nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, butter or shortening, egg, and vanilla until creamy.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until light brown.
Do not overcook.
Cool slightly before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fried zucchini patties
directions: Shred zucchini and squeeze out excess water.
In bowl, add zucchini, egg, onion, mint, salt, pepper and enough flour to make a thick batter.
Heat oil in fry pan and drop batter into hot oil using a big tablespoon. Make little pancakes.
Fry until golden brown and then turn over.
Drain on paper towel.
Finish using batter.
Great on sandwiches or as a side dish.

title: meat and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions together.
Pour off excess grease.
Add salt, pepper and soup.
Stir and pour in pan.
Cover with potatoes and bake.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix together with mixer.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix and spread on 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: swiss steak
directions: Thinly slice steak across the grain into strips.
Lightly coat with flour.
In a large skillet, brown steak, half at a time, in butter.
Return all meat to skillet.
Add tomato.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, except blueberries.
Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with blueberries.
Add the remaining batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: nana's excellent cookies
directions: To beaten eggs, add sugar and shortening. Then add milk, baking soda, salt and flavoring. Stir flour in by hand. Amount is approximate. Add enough flour to make cookies roll well. Cut out desired shapes. Sprinkle with colored sugar, if desired, before baking. Or cookies may be decorated with icing, sprinkles, raisins, etc. after baking. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain potatoes; microwave until mashable with fork.
Mix well with granulated sugar, eggs, 1 stick oleo and vanilla.
Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/2 cup semi-melted oleo and pecans.
Put this topping on the potato mixture in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until crunchy.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in glass baking dish.
Pour apple juice over meat until half covered.
Lightly salt and pepper and sprinkle with thyme.
Sprinkle chopped garlic over each pork chop.
Place 3 or 4 apple slices on each.
Cover tightly, bake at 325 degrees for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place wings on shallow baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Spoon mixture over wings, turning to coat wings all over.
Cover with foil. Bake 15 minutes.
Remove foil.
Turn wings over and bake 15 more minutes, uncovered.

title: christmas casserole cookies(date ball)
directions: Beat eggs with rotary beater.
Add sugar; beat well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Turn into an ungreased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While still hot, beat well with wooden spoon.
Cool; form into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Decorate if you wish.

title: cheese roll
directions: Put room temperature cream cheese in a large bowl.
Add all sauces.
Mix together with hands or use the dough hooks on an electric mixer.
Mix well.
Shape into 2 log rolls or one large ball.
Roll in pecan pieces.
Wrap in wax paper or aluminum foil to store in fridge.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Mix all ingredients with the 1/2 cup milk.
Put in a
9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pizza soup
directions: Combine sausage, onions, and bell pepper in soup pot.
Saute until sausage is fully cooked.
Drain excess grease.
Add mushrooms, pizza sauce, tomatoes, and water.
Cook over medium-high heat for about 10 minutes.
Stir in the Parmesan and keep hot until time to serve.
Top each serving of hot soup with a generous sprinkling of mozzarella cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french cream frosting
directions: Boil together sugar and water; cook to thread stage.
Cream powdered sugar, egg and shortening together.
Add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add sugar water.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. Add the mayonnaise, warm water and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: veal or chicken marsala
directions: Cooking Time: 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat off.
Combine all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding and juice until thick. Pour over fruit. Use your own judgement on the amount of fruit needed.

title: potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes (cooked); drain water off.
Add French dressing; let set for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Will keep well in refrigerator for several days.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain off grease.
Blend in ketchup (enough to coat the meat).
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Break cheese in half and cover the top of the meat mixture.
Place drained green beans on top of cheese.
Cover with mashed potatoes. Heat through.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Roll in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot fat in heavy kettle.
Cover with hot water and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add other ingredients. Simmer for an additional 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: oyster cracker mix
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Microwave 3 minutes. Stir 1 or 2 times while microwaving.
Store mix in tins!
Great party snack with beer - rah!

title: kiss cookies
directions: Mix ingredients well; make into 1-inch balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Place Kiss in center of each ball.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry bacon; set aside.
Peel, cube and boil potatoes and onions.
When potatoes are tender, add milk, salt and pepper. Cook 10 minutes more.
When it thickens, add crumbled up bacon.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Drop onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: fruit and ginger ale salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water, orange juice, ginger ale; let congeal slightly.
Add fruit salad, chill until firm.
Serve over lettuce.
Serves 12.

title: western baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Keep electric pan on low and let simmer.
When hot, serve.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix together.
Pour into foil lined muffin cups.
Freeze. Serve slightly thawed.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Cut each potato in 8 wedges and bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: godfather chicken
directions: Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Put dried beef on bottom of pan in single layer.
Place chicken breasts on top of dried beef.
Cut bacon in half and lay on top of chicken.

title: upside-down blueberry pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in Pyrex dish. Cover and spread blueberries over the butter or margarine.
Mix pancake mix and water until smooth.
Pour over blueberries; cover completely.
Bake about 18 minutes.
Loosen edges with knife and cut into squares.
Invert on plates and serve with warm syrup.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with half of pastry; set aside. Combine berries, sugar, flour, lemon juice and salt in a bowl; toss well.
Spoon berry mixture into pastry lined pie plate.
Dot mixture with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry to 1/8-inch thickness and cut into 10 (10 x 1/2-inch) strips.
Arrange strips in lattice design over pie and trim edges; seal and flute.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: reeses peanut butter cups
directions: Mix crumbs and sugar.
Melt peanut butter and 1 1/2 sticks oleo.
Mix with crumbs and sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Be sure to press down firmly.
Melt 1/2 cup oleo with chocolate chips and spread on top.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: party punch cooler
directions: Soften ice cream and sherbet. Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: fresh strawberry or peach pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, add 1 cup water and cook until thick and clear.
Take from heat and add Jell-O, mix well and cool.
Add a few drops of red food coloring, if not as red as you like.
Cap berries or fruit and put in baked pie shell.
Pour Jell-O mixture over fruit and chill.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: moon drops
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Place slices of bread in casserole dish.
Beat eggs and pour on top.
Add cheese (Cheddar) and meat of your choice.
Add dash of salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: wildly delicious turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with the chilled rice. Cover with Italian dressing to taste & enjoy.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; let stand, uncovered, for at least 6 hours or overnight.
Store in airtight containers.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain artichoke hearts and mash with fork.
Add cheese and mayonnaise; mix well.
Put in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour, sugar and vanilla, mixing thoroughly.
Blend in chips.
Drop by teaspoon and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes. Cool on cookie sheet 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and transfer to rack to cool completely.
Yields 14 dozen.

title: quickie ham and swiss cheese sandwiches
directions: Combine margarine, mustard, poppy seed and onion flakes.
Melt in microwave or in small saucepan.
Stir well.
Split onion rolls and spread with margarine mixture.
Add ham and cheese slices. Wrap in plastic wrap and microwave for approximately 30 seconds.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: *If roasted, salted peanuts used, omit salt and add peanuts after first four minutes of cooking.

title: grandma's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add egg yolks one at a time. Add soda to flour. Add sour cream to sugar mixture, then add flour. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan.

title: ann's rice
directions: Mix rice, water, bouillon cubes and onion soup mix.
Cut margarine in pieces and scatter on top.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be doubled and will still fit in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: bolognese pork loin braised in milk
directions: Heat butter and oil over medium-high heat in a casserole with lid in which meat will fit snugly.
When butter foam subsides, add pork fat side down.
Brown meat thoroughly on all sides, lowering heat if butter starts to brown.
Add salt and pepper and a little milk; wait until it becomes caramel color, then add enough milk to immerse 2/3 of the pork.
Reduce heat to medium; cover casserole leaving top slightly ajar.
Cook slowly for approximately 2 hours or until meat is easily pierced with fork.
Turn and baste meat occasionally, adding any remaining milk.
When meat is cooked, remove it to platter and keep warm.
Milk in casserole should have coagulated into small nut-brown clusters.
If not, raise heat to high, cook uncovered briskly until milk further reduces and darkens.
Skim off fat and discard, being careful not to remove any coagulated milk clusters.
Add warm water, turn heat to high, boil away all water while scraping and loosening all cooking residue in casserole.
Taste and correct seasonings; remove trussing.
Carve into 3/8-inch thick slices.
Spoon sauce over pork and serve immediately.

title: toffee cake
directions: Spread the above mixture on a greased cookie sheet (press with hand).
Bake until golden brown at 350°.
Melt a package of chocolate chips and spread on while hot and sprinkle with nuts (pecans).
Cool and cut in squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: almond bark goodies
directions: Melt almond bark and oil together, add all other ingredients and drop on waxed paper.

title: chunky oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except chunks) in a large bowl until well blended.
Stir in chunks, drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies start to brown (do not overbake).
Cool 1 minute; remove to wire rack.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: mamaw's lillie peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together well. Roll into balls and press with a fork. Bake 10 minutes at 350° or until brown. Cool 10 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine and press into dish (I use an 8 x 8-inch dish).
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese very well.
Spread on first layer and chill.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, cornstarch and pineapple juice together.
Cook over low to medium heat, stirring until clear.
Cool.
Add pineapple and spread over second layer.

title: kids-love-it chili
directions: In large saucepan, brown ground beef over medium-high heat. Drain.

title: evelyn's chili relleno casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Layer washed green chilies, onion and cheese in at least two layers.
Mix milk, eggs and flour.
Pour over chili mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: lemon parfait
directions: In a small heavy stainless steel or enameled saucepan combine the lemon juice, the grated lemon rind, the egg yolks and 1/2 cup of granulated sugar.
Beat the mixture until it is well combined and cook it over moderate heat, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Do not let the mixture boil.
Transfer the mixture to a large bowl and let it cool.
In a bowl beat the egg whites with the cream of tartar and a pinch of salt until they hold soft peaks.
Add the remaining 1/2 cup sugar, 1 to 2 tablespoons at a time, beating and beat the meringue until it holds stiff peaks. Fold the meringue into the lemon mixture.

title: sauteed baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake potatoes for 1 hour.
Break in half and scoop out pulp.
Mash and add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Mash until smooth.
In heavy black iron skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Put potato pulp into skillet and spread in a flat cake.
It is best when it is at least 1-inch thick.
Saute very slowly until golden brown.
Turn and brown on other side. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine. Top evenly with coconut, then sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cheeseburger casserole(club member: amanda speed)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Spread half of mixture in an ungreased casserole dish. Top with cheese and biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sloppy rice
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion, green pepper and chili powder.
Add rice.
Stir until glazed.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Cover and cook until broth is absorbed, about 10 minutes. Add tomatoes; cook 5 minutes longer or until liquid is absorbed and rice cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate meat for 1 hour. Place on drying trays.
Dry at 145° for 6 to 8 hours.
(See your dehydrator for recommended time.)
Turn meat once during the drying period.
Meat is ready when it bends like a green willow without breaking.
Long term storage should be in the refrigerator.

title: cheese ball by gigi
directions: Mix and make into 2 balls. Put in refrigerator until cold. Then roll in nuts.

title: cold crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix into loaf; put in middle of pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine and press firmly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Mix well and pour onto top of crust.
Bake 50 minutes at 300° until set in center.
Top with sour cream and return to oven for 5 more minutes.
Cool before refrigerating.

title: favorite meat casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and green peppers.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Place in large flat pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let sit overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: sugarless fruit cobbler
directions: Empty fruit and juice into an ungreased 2-quart baking dish and sprinkle sweetener and cinnamon over the top.
Moisten biscuit mix with enough water to form a soft dough and drop by spoonfuls on top of fruit.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until top is brown.

title: mexican pecan candy
directions: Mix 2 1/2 cups sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Melt 1/2 cup sugar; add to milk and sugar.
Cook to medium ball in cold water. Add vanilla and butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool until set.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine flour, oil and peanut butter in a bowl.
Gradually add milk using just enough to form a soft dough.
Knead several minutes.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch.
Cut out and place on oiled baking sheet.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: spiced tea
directions: Put red hots and cinnamon sticks in top of coffeepot (coffee maker).
Pour apple cider into coffee maker and perk.
Makes 12 cups.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix by hand.
Add 6 ounce package chocolate chips.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: texas chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer for 5 minutes (will be thick). Fold in chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with glaze or icing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Cook rice.
Mix together.
Add cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese log
directions: In
a mixing bowl combine cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, milk, steak sauce and butter.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy. Chill
slightly.
Shape.
Place chopped nuts on waxed paper; gently
roll
cheese
over	nuts
to coat.	Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: very good casserole
directions: In a large frypan, saute peppers, celery, onion and ground meat in butter.
Add salt.
Reduce heat; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, canned soup and sauces; cook 5 minutes.
Cook noodles by box directions; drain.
Turn noodles into a 14 x 10 x 2 1/2-inch roasting pan.
Add sauce mixture and gently mix.
Add grated cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: pork chop-rice bake
directions: Brown chops in shortening.
Spread rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve one tablespoon of seasoning from envelope of onion soup mix.
Sprinkle remaining soup mix and onion over rice. Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid and distribute mushrooms over rice.
Add hot water to reserved liquid to total 3 cups and pour over rice.
Arrange browned chops on top of rice and sprinkle rice with reserved seasoning from dry soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until just tender.
Remove foil and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir together.
Best if let set in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: an extraordinary treat that is hard to beat
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, peanut butter, vanilla and egg; beat well. Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda to mixture.
Mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Mix in pitcher or pan to pour.
Pour corn meal mixture into 6 cups boiling water slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Cover; continue cooking over low heat 5 minutes.
Pour into loaf pans.
Refrigerate.
Slice, roll in flour and fry in butter or shortening (use high heat).

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix with broccoli.
Add rice, soup and cheese.
Mix together and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: st. john's punch
directions: Dissolve lemonade mix and sugar in 2 quarts of hot water. Stir until all sugar and mix are completely dissolved.
Add fruit juices and remaining water.
Freeze until slushy.
Yield: 75 servings.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix corn meal and whole wheat flour.
Mix molasses with sour milk and add dry ingredients. Steam 2 hours in greased tins.
Cover tightly.

title: granny's peanut butter fudge
directions: Stir sugars and milk in pan and bring to a boil. Let stand a minute and then add jar of marshmallow cream; stir quickly. Then add peanut butter. Pour into buttered dish and let stand to harden.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Cream butter, sugars, beaten egg and liquids.
Add to the dried ingredients and fold in the chips. Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy potato bisque
directions: In large pot, melt butter or margarine.
Add onions and celery and cook until soft.
Add potatoes, parsley, salt, pepper and broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 30 minutes).
Stir in milk and heat. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of cornstarch for desired consistency of bisque.
Cook and stir until soup thickens.
Do not boil.
Season with salt and pepper to desired taste.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and let stand 15 minutes. Meanwhile cut lard into flour and baking powder. Mix all ingredients together. Spread crust in 8x8 greased pan. Pour rhubarb mixture over crust. Sprinkle top with 1/2 c. sugar and 1/2 tsp. cinnamon mixture. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites; add sugar, coconut and nuts.
Add cornflakes and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Combine ingredients, adding milk a little at a time.
Mix well and frost cake.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken in salted water with onions and carrots.
Cool and cut into bite sized pieces.
Cook broccoli and cool.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, wine, sour cream, mushrooms, spices and parsley.
Place broccoli in greased casserole.
