Cover with chicken pieces.
Pour sauce over them. Sprinkle with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan drops
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
With a spoon, stir in sugar and vanilla.
Add pecan halves; stir until coated.
Take pecan halves out individually and place on ungreased cookie sheet, 1/2-inch apart.
Bake in a 200° oven until slightly browned.

title: chocolate angel roll
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Spread half of batter on each of 2 jelly roll pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Loosen cake from edges, invert on towels generously sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Trim off stiff edges of cake.
While hot, carefully roll each cake and towel from narrow end.
Cool on wire rack.
Beat milk and pudding until blended. Stir chopped pecans and chopped candy into pudding mixture. Reserve 3/4 cup whipped topping.
Fold remaining topping into pudding mixture.
Unroll 1 cake and remove towel.
Spread 1/2 the pudding over the cake.
Repeat for other cake.
Roll up.
Garnish with the chocolate topping and rest of whipped cream.
Slice with electric knife.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 egg and blend well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix icing and softened cream cheese until well blended.
Take out 1/2 cup and reserve for later.
Take rest of icing and 2 eggs, beat with mixer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cool and ice with 1/2 cup icing that you put aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients (except additonal ketchup); pour in a shallow pan.
Cover completely with additional ketchup.
Cook at 325° for approximately 1 hour or until browned.
Drain juice; serve on platter.
Serves approximately 8.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix everything except sauce. Blend well and fold into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with sauce before serving.

title: cider wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 20 minutes or longer, until spice taste is definite. Strain. Serve hot or cold.
Serves 25.

title: potato soup
directions: Make according to the amount you are serving.

title: pineapple pork chops(light)
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Place chops in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Mix pineapple juice, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Pour over chops.
Cover and refrigerate, turning chops once or twice for 8 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Top each chop with pineapple slice.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake until done, about 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 more minutes.
Remove chops and pineapple to serving platter.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 4 servings, 300 calories each.

title: blue cheese salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a quart jar.
Let sit for an hour or so.
Refrigerate.
Set out a bit before dinner to soften.

title: angel pudding cake
directions: Tear cake into bite-size pieces and place in oblong baking dish.
Mix together pudding mix, yogurt and milk until smooth. Pour on top of angel cake bites and top with sliced (fresh or frozen) strawberries.
Chill before serving.
Makes good "quick and easy" low-cal dessert.

title: pepitas(toasted pumpkin seeds)
directions: Combine pumpkin seeds, oil and salt; spread in a shallow baking pan.
Toast in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, stirring once or twice. Drain on paper towel.
Store Pepitas in a tightly covered container.
Makes 2 cups.

title: farmer's casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart square baking dish. Arrange potatoes evenly in the bottom of the dish. Sprinkle with cheese, ham and green onion.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 3 (9-inch) layer pans with waxed paper.
Microwave chocolate and water in large bowl on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Mix first three ingredients well. Turn out on floured surface. Fold so that all sides are covered with flour. Roll out or pat dough to desired thickness (approx. 1/4 inch). Place 2 tablespoons oil in iron skillet. Cut out biscuits and place in skillet. Cover tops with remaining oil. Bake until golden brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Make filling by sauteing onion in butter; add chicken. Combine 1 cup salsa and tomato sauce.
Add to chicken.
Add sour cream and salt.
Dip tortillas in milk.
Spread filling on tortillas and roll.
Place seam side down on baking dish; pour remaining cream over and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Put in uncooked pie crust and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frosted 7-up fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; cool.
Add 7-Up and chill until partially set.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows.
Chill until firm in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with favorite whipped topping and sprinkle with shredded American cheese.
Enjoy!

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix Hawaiian Punch, ginger ale, orange juice and water. Add sherbet, in chunks, on top to float and serve.

title: princess pie
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Beat in 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
Add remaining milk and lemon pudding mix.
Beat with mixer for approximately 1 minute.
Pour into crust and chill 1 hour or until set.
When ready to serve, top with chilled and well drained fruit cocktail.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.

Cut in shortening. Combine egg and milk. Add to flour mixture, stirring quickly to make a soft dough. Mix butter, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. Spread over bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan. Arrange apple slices over sugar mixture.
Spread dough on top of apples, patting out to cover bottom layers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Invert onto serving plate. Serve warm with cream or whipped cream, as desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dilly salmon appetizer
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid; flake.
Soften gelatin in reserved salmon liquid.
Stir in chicken broth.
Heat to dissolve gelatin completely.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: garlic ribs
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch squares.
In a big bowl, mix soy sauce, garlic, pepper and brown sugar.
Add meat.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Marinate 2 hours or more.
Mix flour and cornstarch. Dip drained meat pieces in mixture.
Deep-fry until meat floats. The longer it marinates the better the meat tastes.
Serves 4 people.
Preparation time:
2 1/2 hours.

title: low country shrimp and grits
directions: Prepare grits recipe, using full amount of cheese.
Season to taste with black pepper; keep warm.
Peel shrimp.
Dice bacon and saute in skillet lightly.
Add enough peanut oil to bacon fat to make layer 1/8-inch deep.
When hot, add shrimp in even layer, turning as they color.
Add mushrooms, garlic and green onions. Stir and cook for several minutes.
Season with lemon juice, Tabasco, parsley, salt and pepper.
Divide grits on 4 plates. Spoon shrimp over top and serve immediately.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients (can juices, too).
Stir to mix.
Simmer until seasonings blend.

title: scotcheroo bars
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in saucepan.
Heat until sugar dissolves, but do not boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease pie plate 10 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Mix apples and spices.
Turn into pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour over apples.
Sprinkle with Streusel.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash, chicken soup, carrot and onion together with 1/2 cup of stuffing.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup stuffing on top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir into corn.
Mix hot milk, butter and eggs.
Add to corn.
Grease a baking dish.
Put all in and then spread cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except sugar.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.
Serves 2 1/2 dozen.

title: nut brownies
directions: Blend on top of stove the margarine and sugar until mixed; do not cook. Remove from stove. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients together; add to pan, then add nuts. Pour into a greased 8-inch pan. Bake for 25 minutes. Very moist brownies.

title: fresh strawberry pie(go strawberry picking one day in june for fun and flavor.)
directions: Cook mashed berries, water and sugar/cornstarch in saucepan over medium low heat.
Stir frequently.
When mixture is clear and thick, add lemon juice.
Let stand to cool.

title: nestle crunch pie
directions: Melt Nestle bar on low heat or in microwave.
Fold in Cool Whip, then put in pie crust.
Cool in refrigerator until firm.

title: rita moreno's casserole
directions: Brown pepper, onion and garlic.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add raisins and remaining ingredients.
This can be served over rice.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
In 4-quart pot, combine first 8 ingredients and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mushrooms will make liquid.
Add spaghetti sauce, pizza sauce and water.

title: sour cream chocolate frosting
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in microwave 2 minutes on High. Remove and blend in sour cream, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar until spreading consistency.

title: mom's spanish rice
directions: Heat butter/oil in saucepan; add onion, green pepper and rice. Cook and stir over high heat until lightly browned. Add tomatoes, water, salt and pepper. Mix well. Bring gently to boil. Cover tightly. Lower heat and simmer gently for 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: coconut cherry cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream.
Stir dry ingredients together. Blend in shortening mixture.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful, about 2 inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly brown.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until just barely tender and drain.
Cool. Add onion,
green
pepper
and celery with some leaves.
Cook tomato soup, vinegar, white sugar, salt and oil until boiling. Pour
hot mixture
over carrots, onion, celery and green peppers.
Stir well
to mix flavors.
Will keep at least 4 weeks in refrigerator. Serve cold on buffet table or as a relish.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple and juice. Drain mandarin oranges and add.
Let Jell-O set.

title: quick and easy hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add soup, sour cream or yogurt and seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: layered green salad
directions: Place the first 6 ingredients in layers in order given in large salad bowl.
On top of salad ingredients, spread the mayo and sprinkle sugar, seasoned salt and garlic powder.
Cover with heavy layer of cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Make each flavor
and let it set up before adding next layer (per instructions).
Use a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring milk & sugar to boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes. Add Jif and stir just until melted. Add butter and vanilla; beat until smooth. Put into greased 9 x 13 pan. Let cool to room temperature before cutting.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Open the chilies and layer half of them in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cover with half of the Cheddar, then half the Jack.
Spread the second half of the chilies in a layer over the cheese, then cover with remaining cheeses.

title: stuffed mushrooms italiano
directions: Remove and finely chop mushroom stems.
Combine dressing, bread crumbs, cheese, parsley and chopped mushroom stems in medium bowl.
Fill each mushroom cap with bread crumb mixture; arrange in shallow baking dish.
Add water to barely cover bottom of dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed baked turkey
directions: Blend onion and all ingredients in a blender until a paste has formed.
Marinate the turkey in this paste overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon onto waxed paper.
Combine eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center springs back when lightly pressed with fingertips.
Cool on wire rack.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, oil and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Beat in the yeast and slightly beaten egg.
Gradually add remaining 2 cups of flour.
Work well.
Put in greased bowl.
Turn once.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours or double in bulk.
Mash down and shape into rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake in a 400° oven.
Makes one large pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer seasoned with salt and pepper.
Remove from bone. Reserve 1 1/2 quarts broth and boil shells in broth.
Do not drain. Saute pepper and onions in margarine.
To the shells, add mushrooms and cheese (cut in small pieces).
Add tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Stir lightly and put in large greased casserole dish. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: twin mountain biscuits
directions: Use an
ordinary
biscuit
recipe, but add 1 tablespoon sugar in
place of shortening ordinarily used and add 2 tablespoons peanut
butter.
This
is
for
recipes using 2 cups of flour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 3-quart dish, pour 1 can of soup in bottom.
Mix green beans and water chestnuts; place on soup.
Pour second can of soup on top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Heat and serve warm.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat
between each addition. Add vanilla.
Alternately add the dry ingredients
and buttermilk.
Put batter in a greased tube pan. Bake
at 325° until light golden brown, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Cream cheese mixture:
Beat together the softened cream cheese and butter.
Add the sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Set aside.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: *Use any fruit:
crushed pineapple, peaches, fruit cocktail, Mandarin oranges, etc.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin pans; fill 2/3 full.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press the rolls into jelly roll pan.
Bake until golden brown (15 minutes at 350°).
Cool.
Mix together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on crust.
Sprinkle cut vegetables on top along with cheese.
May use a combination or all the pepperoni, bacon bits, cauliflower, green peppers, carrots, tomatoes, onions, mushrooms and broccoli.
Make right before and chill.
Cut into squares.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix together all ingredients except Certo, bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Add Certo to mix, pour into jars immediately.
Pepper will rise to top.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off bones.
Melt margarine and stir in corn bread crumbs.
Put in a layer of crumbs, then layer of chicken.
Pour in 1/2 of soup that has been diluted with broth. Put in another layer of crumbs, a layer of chicken and rest of soup.
Top with crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: carob pie
directions: Blend smooth.
Cook in saucepan until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Decorate with coconut.
Chill.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Add cheese mixture by hand and freeze.
Freeze in a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Pour macaroni into baking dish.
Add cheese, milk and butter.
Mix well.
Sprinkle a little cheese on top.
Put in a 350° oven until cheese is melted and turning a little brown.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Mix and sift the dry ingredients (except the last three). Stir in milk, shortening and nuts.
Put in a pan.
Spread top with the last three ingredients.
Cover with 1 3/4 cups very hot water. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful in deep fryer at 350° until golden brown.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: cream of wheat cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cook slowly 15 minutes.
Pour in cake pan and cool completely.
Cut into squares or diamonds.
Beat 1 egg and dip squares in egg, then in bread crumbs.
Deep fry until brown.
Drain.
Serve hot or cold.
Delicious on cold nights.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon in large bowl, toss well.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour dressing over broccoli mix, chill and serve.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs and sugar and beat well.
Stir in butter.
Add milk and beat until smooth.
Stir in corn.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Blend well and turn into a 1-quart greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Serves 6.

title: easy pizza burgers
directions: Cook beef until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain off pan drippings.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Cook over low heat about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Place half the cheese strips on bun halves.
Top with meat mixture and remaining cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.

title: french pastry
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening until "corn meal" consistency.
In separate container, blend egg, water and vinegar. Sprinkle over flour mixture and toss with fork.
Let stand at least 10 minutes before rolling out.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind 1 gallon (measurement before grinding) green tomatoes. Put on stove and let get hot.
Strain through colander.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 1/2 hour.
Put relish in sterilized pint jars while hot.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix first 6 ingredients in with 1/4 cup Manwich sauce. Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Drain excess fat.
Spread mustard over top of loaf.
Pour on remaining Manwich sauce.
Bake 35 minutes longer.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with cake mix and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Bake 1/2 of this in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 5 or 6 minutes. Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Spread on cake; sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over cake.
Dot remaining batter over cake, then bake for 30 more minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Add the Knox gelatine mixture to the orange Jell-O. Add the sherbet to the gelatins and mix together. Add the pineapple and oranges.
Pour in Jell-O mold and place in refrigerator until congealed.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and corn syrup together in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave for 4 minutes at 100% power.
Add peanuts and stir well.
Microwave for 4 minutes at 100% power.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Microwave 30 seconds to 2 minutes at 100% power.
Watch carefully.
Add baking soda.
Stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture at once onto buttered cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix well and let congeal.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Cook blackberries, water and 5 cups sugar until thickened.
Mix flour, oleo, milk, eggs and 3 tablespoons sugar to soft dough. Drop by teaspoons into boiling blackberries.
Cover and let cook 5 minutes (work quickly).

Serve with cream, Cool Whip or ice cream. Or make dumplings out of canned biscuits, rolled out and cut up, or biscuits can be snipped into 8 pieces with kitchen shears, letting each piece drop into boiling blackberries.
Cook as directed.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 70 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Beat eggs in a large bowl; add the next eight ingredients and mix well. Stir in 2 cups cheese. Pour into a greased 13X9X2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour. Top with remaining cheese. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving. Garnish with peppers, if desired. Yield: 12-15 servings.

title: dad's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease Sporto Ball pans with vegetable shortening and dust with flour or use vegetable pan spray.
For easier handling, place pans on cookie sheet.

title: chocolate haystacks(no bake)
directions: Mix well.
Quickly spoon onto wax paper to cool.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Partially thaw and mash strawberries; add to Jell-O as the cold liquid.
Place mixture in refrigerator until shaky.
Cut cake in 1-inch pieces and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour Jell-O mixture over cake in pan and refrigerate until firm.
When ready to serve, cover top with Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin ice cream dessert
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press in a 9 inch square pan. Combine soft vanilla ice cream and the other five ingredients. Place on the crust.
Cover and freeze.
Remove 20 minutes before serving.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: mac-spam casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Add milk to soup and mix well.
Heat, but do not boil.
May add cheese as desired.
Stir until melted. Add macaroni and diced Spam in casserole dish. Pour soup over top. Place slices of cheese or onions over casserole. Bake at 350° until brown and bubbling.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: 1. Drain juice off kidney and butter beans. Mix together.
2. Place into 3 qt. casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 1
hour.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Beginning with lettuce, layer each item in order listed in large casserole dish. Other items may be added or substituted. Salad should be made and refrigerated overnight. Makes 10 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix meats together.
Soak bread in cream about 5 minutes. Cook onion in 1 tablespoon of butter until tender.
Combine meat, crumb mixture, egg, onion and seasonings.
Beat vigorously until fluffy with electric mixer.
Form in 1 1/2-inch balls.
(Mixture will be soft.)
Brown in 2 tablespoons of butter, shaking skillet to keep balls round.
Remove meat balls.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add beaten eggs, melted butter and other ingredients.
Pour into three Pet-Ritz pie shells and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat oil and sugar together.
Add 2 beaten eggs and 3 bananas; mash until creamy.
In separate bowl, sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to the first mixture with milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured loaf pan for 60 minutes.

title: chili beans(microwave)
directions: Crumble beef in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in onion and green pepper.
Cover with glass lid.
Cook in oven (microwave) on High for 6 minutes.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Re-cover. Cook 20 to 25 minutes on Medium.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: russian vegetable borscht
directions: Heat oil in a large kettle over medium heat. Add onion, bell pepper and garlic. Cook for 5 minutes; stir frequently. Add remaining ingredients, except vinegar. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add vinegar. Chill and re-heat. Serve. Makes 8 (1 1/2-cup) servings. Prep time: 1 hour.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients. Mix with your hands until it is blended thoroughly. Use a loaf pan approximately 4 x 4 x 12 as a mold. (The mixture will make four loaves.) Press the meat firmly into the pan, then level it off. Run a knife around the sides, then turn out the loaf, upside down, on a dry baking sheet. Rub a liberal dousing of catsup all over the top and sides of each loaf. Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for 60 minutes. If there's room in the oven, cook them all at once.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine and melt over low heat the 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 sticks butter or margarine.
In a Ziploc bag, mix 2/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.

title: "hot" turkey chili
directions: Simmer the first 8 ingredients for 20 minutes to make stock. May need to add some chicken bouillon (5 teaspoons).
Drain, cool and skim fat.
Reduce stock to 3 cups; remove carcus.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread beans on bottom of casserole.
Spread salsa on top of beans.
Sprinkle cheese and half of the olives.
Microwave 5 minutes or bake in oven at 350° until cheese melts and it's heated through.
Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and remaining olives.
Spoon sour cream in center.
Serve warm with Doritos.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and oleo to rolling boil.
Stir in flour. Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball. Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, all at one time.

Continue beating until smooth. Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until puffed and golden. Cool from draft. Cut off tops. Pull out any filaments of dough. Carefully fill puffs with vanilla cream pudding.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla together.
Add to dry ingredients along with the sour cream and zucchini.
Add nuts and/or raisins.
Bake in two greased loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caroline marsh's quick and easy banana loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar together in large mixing bowl.
Put peeled bananas into small bowl and add baking soda to bananas. Mash bananas and soda together.
Add to butter and sugar.
Mix in all remaining ingredients.

title: microwave meat loaf(hamburger or turkey burger)
directions: Chop onions and bell pepper. Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Place in microwave dish.
(I use a browning dish which has a heating element in the bottom that works real well.) Cover dish with lid. Cook on High for 20 to 30 minutes or until it is done, depending on your microwave.
If you desire, you can add spices for meat loaf. I have done this in the past; very good, quick and easy.

title: godfather's spaghetti sauce with italian sausage and red wine
directions: In a large pot, heat oil over low heat, add garlic and onion and cook until translucent.
Stir in wine.
Add tomatoes and paste (rinse can with water and add to pot).
Add basil, salt and sugar to taste and stir.
When sauce comes to light boil, add sausage (uncooked) and simmer over low heat for 3 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally and adding water if sauce gets too thick.
Correct seasonings in last hour and partly cover pot.
Serve over spaghetti and drink the rest of the wine.
Flavor improves if refrigerated overnight.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions on box.

title: holiday fragrance
directions: Cut orange and lemon peels into small pieces.
Add remaining ingredients; fill with water to cover.
Simmer as long as you desire.
Remember to add water so that it doesn't boil away.

title: cheese club sandwich
directions: Set oven control to broil or 550°.
For each sandwich, broil bread slice 5 inches from heat until golden brown on one side, turn.
Broil on second side until golden.
Spread second side with margarine or butter.
Top with tomato slice.
Place bacon on tomato and top with a slice of cheese.
Broil until cheese has melted.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: Cut chocolate in small pieces.
Place all ingredients except vanilla in a saucepan.
Bring slowly to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil briskly without stirring for 1 to 2 minutes.
Do not overboil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat, adding vanilla, until thick enough to spread.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add fruits and juices.
Pour 1/2 into 10 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Smooth sour cream over gelatin.
Sprinkle nuts over sour cream.
Cover with remaining gelatin mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce bed with dash of sour cream and fresh strawberries.

title: surprise nut square
directions: Mix eggs, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda. Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased, oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Make crust and line bottom of dish.
Beat Dream Whip.
Add sugar to cheese and cream.
Then fold sugar and cheese into the Dream Whip.
Pour over crust, top this with the cherries and chill.

title: amazing rice
directions: Mix uncooked rice and gumbo soup in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Add chicken broth.
Put margarine in center.
Cover with tight lid. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Fluff with fork when done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook until blended or bake in a casserole with cracker crumbs on top.

title: lentil shepherd's pie
directions: Mash cooked lentils.
Add onion and seasonings.
Mash potatoes and add milk, salt and McKay's seasoning to taste.
Beat until fluffy.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 10 ingredients.
Transfer to a greased 2 1/2 qt. baking dish.

title: popped cran-tea
directions: Keep juices in refrigerator when purchased (not freezer). Combine cranberries in water with cinnamon sticks and cloves. Boil until cranberries pop.
Pour through strainer into large container.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add refrigerated juices and water.
Stir until mixed.
Serve while still hot.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Fix rice as box says.
While rice is cooking, mix taco mix, Ro-Tel tomatoes, olives, onion, mushrooms, soup and chicken, drained.
Mix well.
Add rice and mix.
Spread in dish and put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (or until fully heated and cheese is melted).

title: susan's chili
directions: Boil beef broth in 4-quart pot.
Slowly add beef and separate into small pieces.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add everything else except tomato paste and beans.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Thicken with tomato paste as needed.
Add beans if desired.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6.

title: rabbit
directions: Wrap rabbit in strips of pork fat and put in roasting pan with carrot, mandarin slices, chopped shallots, herbs and white wine. Roast in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
After cooking 30 minutes, add mandarin juice.
Remove rabbit, discard pork fat, strain sauce, pour over rabbit.
Flame with vodka or gin.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli vinaigrette
directions: Over high heat, bring large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add broccoli.
Cook until just tender, about 5 minutes, adding red onion during last 1 minute of cooking time.
Drain well. Meanwhile, in large serving bowl, stir together vinegar, honey, mustard, salt and pepper until salt dissolves.
Gradually stir in oil until mixture thickens.
Stir in broccoli-onion mixture until coated in vinaigrette.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving to allow flavors to blend.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cabbage and garbanzo stew
directions: Slice cabbage, dice onion and tomato.
In a frying pan, saute onion and tomato.
Add cabbage and steam until cooked.
Add garbanzo beans and season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: wasps' nests
directions: Butter and flour cookie sheets. Set oven to 350°. Cook together until syrup spins a thread (240°) 1/4 cup sugar and water. Remove from heat. Add chocolate chips or M&M's. Beat egg whites until very stiff. Add sugar by spoonfuls while beating constantly. Add the chocolate and almonds to egg white mixture. Put 1/2 teaspoon of dough on cookie sheets. Bake for about 25 minutes (until dry). Let stand 10 minutes and remove.

title: creole shrimp stew
directions: Heat oil in large pot and gradually stir in flour.
Cook and stir over medium heat until chocolate brown in color.
Add onions and garlic and cook until soft.
Pour tomatoes, corn and water into pot.
Add bay leaf and parsley.
Season to taste.
Simmer at least 1 hour, adding water if necessary to achieve desired consistency.
Soup may be made ahead to this point and refrigerated.
Add shrimp and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chopped pickles
directions: Chop all ingredients and sprinkle salt and let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and wash in cold water.
Cook sugar, vinegar, water and spices (wrapped in cheesecloth) for about 5 minutes, then add well drained ingredients.
Cook until tender, about 1/2 hour.
Put in hot jars; fill with juice and seal.

title: lacy balloons
directions: This is wonderful for making party decorations.

title: pound cake squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs (with spoon, not beater). Spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 3 tablespoons sugar and combine remainder with the softened cream cheese.
Then beat in 2 eggs and vanilla and lemon zest.
Spread over cake mixture and sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While cake is warm, sift reserved sugar on top.
When cool, cut into 15 even portions.

title: oven baked caramel corn
directions: Place first four ingredients into a 2-quart pan; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and soda.
Stir well.
Pour over corn, covering all kernels as much as possible.
Place on 2 large cookie sheets. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a ball.
Roll into chopped pecans.

title: sweet tortilla crisps
directions: Brush tortillas with lite margarine; cut each tortilla with a pizza cutter into 8 wedges.
Place the tortillas on an ungreased baking sheet.
Combine sugar and cinnamon, stirring well. Sprinkle sugar mixture evenly over tortilla wedges.

title: smoked salmon spread-dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Garnish with onion and parsley. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix onions, cucumbers, garlic and salt.
Put 2 trays ice cubes on top.
Leave for 3 hours.
Drain vegetables; take out garlic. Combine rest of ingredients and heat to boiling and add vegetables.
Cook 5 minutes.
Seal in jars and hot bath 5 minutes in rolling boil water.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar for 10 minutes with electric mixer until creamy/fluffy (on creaming butter/sugar speed).
Add eggs and blend.
Reduce speed on mixer to #2 speed (blending).
Alternate flour and milk, beating until well blended.
Add butternut flavoring and blend until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Can be served plain or iced.
Use Butternut Icing or any of your choice.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix chicken, onion, sour cream and 1 can of soup.
Spoon mixture into tortillas and roll up.
Place in a baking dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Pour remaining can of soup over tortillas.
Top with salsa and cheese.
Bake an additional 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, butter and milk and mix, then add remaining ingredients.
Put in dish and bake at 350°.

title: date bars
directions: Mix like pie dough.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Take out a little at a time.
(Keep remaining dough in refrigerator.
Work with cold dough.)
Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Cut and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until firm.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: frozen salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Cut cherries and add to mixture with marshmallows.
Whip the cream and add to mixture.
Fold in crushed pineapple and nuts.
Put in 7 x 11 x 2-inch dish.
Cover with foil and freeze.
Keeps good.
Thaw for short time before serving.
Serves 20 people.

title: better brownies(microwave)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add salt.
Stir in syrup, flour and vanilla. Add nuts and stir to blend well.
Turn into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square microsafe pan or dish.
Microwave on High power for 3 minutes.
Let rest 3 minutes. Repeat on High power for 3 minutes and let rest 3 minutes.
Finally, microwave on High power for 2 more minutes or until batter is set and done to your liking.
Let rest in pan for a couple of minutes or until almost cool.
Cut into squares and remove from pan and garnish with nuts or powdered sugar.

title: awesome punch
directions: Cook water & sugar until dissolved, remove from heat.
Add lemon jello & stir until dissolved.
Add lemonade, orange juice & pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add 1 gal. water.
Put in container & freeze until slush.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients, nuts last.
Spread on cookie sheet lined with foil.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
While cooking stir occasionally.
Let cool.
Spread 1/2 of mixture in bottom of pan. Next, place slices of vanilla ice cream (1/2 gallon); Top with 1 jar Kraft Caramel sauce and with remaining crumbs.

title: gourmet carrots
directions: Steam carrots to desired doneness.
To carrots, add butter, maple syrup and parsley.
Mix so carrots are completely covered. Serve.

title: michal's coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and add 2 cups flour.
Use 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue for chicken and pork chops
directions: Cover chicken or pork with sauce and bake.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In 3 qt. saucepan gradually stir soup into cream cheese.
Add milk, mustard and pepper.
Heat thoroughly over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add pasta, vegetables and Parmesan cheese.
Heat through, stirring often. 4 servings.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese and milk.
Blend together rest of ingredients.
Heat in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal raisin cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl beat butter until light and fluffy.
Add granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until creamy. Add honey, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add oats, coconut and raisins; mix well to evenly distribute ingredients.
Drop by heaping tablespoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: swiss steak with onions
directions: Sift ingredients together and beat into 3 lb round steak cut thick. Pound in until all the flour is taken up. Then brown pieces of steak in 1/3 cup butter or other shortening in frying pan. After browned on both sides put in a casserole dish. Saute 2 cups sliced onions in frying pan till softened. Remove from pan. Rinse pan with 1 cup water and pour over steak pieces. Arrange onions over steak-covered casserole and bake in slow oven 325° for about 2 hours or till tender.

title: cheese cake infosino
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature for 1 hour to soften before starting.
Margarine should be melted when mixed with crackers.
Do not overbeat any of the cheese or sour cream mixtures.

title: bacon and cheese potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and place in a saucepan.
Cover with water. Cook until tender but firm.
Drain and cube.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda in large mixing bowl or pan.
Mix together sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg.
Cream the same way you mix a cake.
Remove beaters and pour in flour mixture.
Mix with your hands like you make up biscuits.
Pour on floured board and roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into squares or any shape you like.
Take a fork and stick holes in each cookie.
Bake at 350° until done.
Should be golden brown in color.

title: mom's caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread dough enough to cut through it.
Cut into 1 or 2 inch pieces.

title: carrots
directions: Mix carrots, soup and cheese together. Add French fried onions on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vanilla crumb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add milk alternately with wafer crumbs.
Add coconut and nuts.
Grease and flour sides of tube pan.
Pour in cake batter.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.

title: miniature pecan tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine.
Add egg and mix.
Mix in sugar and flour.
Mix well.
Place in miniature pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix crushed cookies with melted butter and pat into bottom and sides of 8 or 9 inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: walnut cheese spread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Makes a delicious spread or stuffing.

title: bravo's famous chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium bowl.
Barbecue chicken wings until crispy and well done.
Place chicken wings in bowl with sauce and mix until chicken is coated.
Place back on grill for 5 minutes, then serve.

title: candied yam
directions: Peel and slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle sugar over yams with nutmeg. Squeeze lemon juice over potatoes and slice lemon thinly and place over potatoes.
Cut margarine or butter over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Dissolve sugar in a mug with some hot water.
Add rum.
Add cinnamon stick and a pinch of nutmeg.
Fill mug with boiling water and top with a pat of butter.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple, pie filling and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium-sized bowl.
Recipe may be doubled for company.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread 1 roll of cookie dough onto a pizza pan.
Bake for about 10 to 15 minutes at temperature on cookie dough package.
Let cool.
Mix soft cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Spread on top of cookie, then add halved fruit as desired.
Drain any fruit that might be in any juice.
Fresh fruit is really the best. Serves 10.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix together, flour, eggs, baking powder.
Add enough water to make pastry.
Drop by 1/2 to 1 teaspoon at a time into boiling water for 3 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Add to soups or casseroles.

title: baked sausage and mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook sausage and drain.
Add mushrooms, garlic and sauce.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add pasta to sauce mixture and mix well.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of Mozzarella and 1/2 of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and butter.
Add egg yolks and lemon juice. Then add milk and lastly stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on single crust at 350° until brown on top (approximately 1 hour).

title: angel pie
directions: Mix baking powder and sugar.
Beat egg whites.
Gradually add sugar mixture and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Crush graham crackers into crumbs and mix with chopped pecans.
Fold into the egg whites.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Sprinkle with additional pecans, finely chopped.

title: punch
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Chill and serve.
Makes 100 (4 ounce) servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Bring cold water to full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat; add tea bags all at once.
Let stand for 5 minutes; strain into punch bowl.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Cool at room temperature.
Add juices and water; refrigerate.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and ice.
Garnish with lemon slices topped with sliced red and green cherries.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and beat well. Add vanilla and flour gradually.
Crush potato chips by hand and add last.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
(Keeps well in a tightly closed tin; actually tastes better the second or third day.)
Yield:
9 to 10 dozen.

title: gina's cabbage dish
directions: Arrange medium chopped cabbage in lightly greased baking dish. Brown hamburger, onion, salt, and pepper.
Spread on top of cabbage mixture.
Pour tomato soup over mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour, cocoa, vanilla and salt.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread marshmallow cream over cooled brownies.
In saucepan, melt peanut butter and chocolate chips over low heat.
When melted, stir in cereal.
Spread over marshmallow layer.
Chill before cutting.

title: shirley's yummy yellow cake
directions: Mix and beat.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together, make a loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ann seranne's rib roast of beef
directions: Remove the roast from the refrigerator 2 1/2 hours to 4 hours before cooking.
Preheat oven to 500 degrees.
Place the roast in an open shallow roasting pan, fat side up.
Sprinkle with a little flour and rub the flour into the fat lightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put the roast in the preheated oven and roast 15 minutes per rib, or approximately five minutes cooking time per pound of trimmed, ready-to-cook roast.
When the cooking time is finished, turn off the oven.
Do not open the door at any time.
Allow the roast to remain in the oven until oven is lukewarm, or about two hours.
Roast will have a crunchy brown outside and an internal heat that will be suitable for serving as long as four hours.
Beef will be pink in the middle.
Yield:
Two servings per rib.
To reheat, put meat in a 325 degree oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: waterbagel(makes 1 dozen)
directions: In large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast. Gradually add warm water to dry mix.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Add 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make soft dough.
Turn on board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in oven 20 minutes.
Punch dough down.
Turn onto board; roll into 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Cut dough in 12 strips, 1 x 10-inch each.
Form circle; pinch ends.
Place on greased sheets. Cover; let rise in oven 20 minutes.
Boil 1 3/4-inches depth of water in large shallow pan.
Lower heat and add few bagels at one time.
Simmer 7 minutes.
Remove from water; place on towel to cool.
Cool 5 minutes.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Brush with egg white and water; return to oven 20 minutes more.
Cool on racks.

title: cheddar buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add the cheese and toss.
Stir in buttermilk until mixture is moistened.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface; knead 8-10 times.
Pat or roll to 1 inch thickness; cut with floured 2 1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15-18 minutes until golden brown.
Yields 6-8 biscuits.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Karo syrup, melted butter, flour and pecans.
Pour
into pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes or until
firm.
This
is
a good pie, not as sweet as most.

title: cucumber hor d'oeuvres
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix.
Spread on rye bread.
Top with cucumber slice and sprinkle on dill weed.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Combine soup and cream cheese on low heat until smooth; add green onions, celery, shrimp, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Dissolve gelatine and add to mixture.
Pour into mold; let stand 24 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: egg custard
directions: Use unbaked deep dish crust.
Scald butter and milk.
Beat eggs and add sugar to eggs.
Add vanilla and milk last.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: rice salad
directions: Bring water and dressing to a boil.
Add rice and cover.
Let set until cool.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 8.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips. Place in a reclosable plastic bag. Add cornstarch and toss to coat. Combine soy sauce, ginger and garlic powder; add to bag and shake well. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joe squares
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Brown ground beef; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, seasoning mix and onion.
Mix well.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate each can of crescent dough into 2 large rectangles.
Press 2 over bottom of dish.
Spoon hot meat mixture over dough.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place remaining rectangles over top of cheese and meat. Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: no peek tri-tip
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Trim and season Tri-Tip.
Place on a rack in a pan.
Cook at 500° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Shut oven off and let Tri-Tip set in oven for 45 minutes.
Don't open oven door until 45 minutes are up.

title: english traditional braised red cabbage with apples(serves 10 to 12 people)
directions: First discard the outer leaves of cabbage, cut it into quarters and remove the hard stalk.
Then shred the rest of the cabbage finely.
In a fairly large casserole, arrange a layer of shredded cabbage, seasoned with salt and pepper, then a layer of chopped onions and apples with a sprinkling of garlic, spices and sugar.
Continue with these alternate layers until everything is in.
Pour in the wine vinegar, then lastly add dots of butter on top.
Put a tight lid on the casserole and let it cook very slowly in the oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, stirring around once or twice during the cooking.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 3 (9-inch) cake pans.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and basil. Stir in chicken broth and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add chicken.
Combine cottage cheese with egg.
Mix well.

title: tutti-frutti roll
directions: Blend all ingredients and shape in a roll and roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.
Also wrap in Saran Wrap or foil.
Slice and serve.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add salt.
Beat eggs slightly and add to this mixture.
Add vanilla.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Spoon sifted flour, sugar and salt in 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Make well in center.
With fork, mix oil and milk until blended; pour into well and mix with fork until flour is moistened.
Press out with hands.
Flute rim and chill.
Prick bottom for baked shell and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk, flour, salt, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add soda.
Cook on hot grill or electric skillet.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients, then add rest of ingredients; mix well with spoon.
Fill floured and greased 1-pound coffee cans 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, sour cream, Kahlua and vegetable oil.
Beat at low speed to blend with electric mixer. Beat 3 to 5 minutes at medium-fast speed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes or until tests done.
Cool on rack for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients; serve 2 teaspoons in 6 ounces of hot water.
Store remaining mix in airtight container.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; bone and tear into bite size pieces.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat broiler.
Stir stuffing mix and water in medium bowl. Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems.
Cook and stir mushroom caps in 3 tablespoons hot margarine until lightly browned. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Cook and stir chopped mushroom stems and peppers in skillet until tender.
Stir into prepared stuffing.
Spoon into mushroom caps.
Drizzle tops with remaining margarine.
Makes 8 appetizer servings.

title: garden fresh pork chops
directions: In medium skillet, melt butter; brown chops.
Add vegetables and basil.
Combine soup mix and water.
Add to vegetables.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 45 minutes or until chops and veggies are tender.
Serves 2 people.

title: alpine "chicken"
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cheese may be added on top the last 10 minutes.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight. Serves 6.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Put scrambled up hamburger in skillet; let it cook thoroughly. In a mixing bowl put mushroom soup, chicken soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies; mix together.
Pour in over hamburger and let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Set aside.
Line bottom of pan with tortilla shells.
Pour half of mixture over shells.
Scramble up chips and put them over 1/2 of mixture.
Put another layer of shells.
Add remainder of mixture.
Add the shredded cheese on top. Cook at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Chop onions.
Cut chicken into pieces approximately 1 x 1/2 x 1/2-inch.
Preheat oil in large frying pan.
Put onions in hot oil and fry on medium heat until golden brown.
Add chicken; fry 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add salt, pepper and sour cream; stir and fry for 3 minutes.
Serve with mashed potatoes. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions; drain.
In large saucepan heat oil; add onion and garlic; cook until tender. Stir in spaghetti sauce; simmer uncovered 15 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
In 15 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna, half the remaining sauce, all the spinach, half the remaining Mozzarella, remaining lasagna and sauce.
Cover. Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 45 minutes).
Uncover; top with remaining Mozzarella and parsley.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: one of my favorite sandwiches
directions: Slice ham to medium thickness.
Set aside.
Dice onion.
Fry onion with small amount of olive oil until onion is browned. Slice tomato in very thin slices.
Slice cheese in thin slices. Toast bread.
Put small amount of cheese on each piece of toast. Alternate several layers of ham, onions and tomato slices.
Add banana peppers if used.
Add small amount of Heinz 57 sauce. Assemble the 2 sandwiches and microwave on Medium-high for 1 minute.

title: fruit candy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Press into buttered pan. Cut into bars.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Brown meat, add onion soup mix, then mix remaining ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. You may add celery to this, if you like.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Stir 2 tablespoons flour into the sugar.
Cream in butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each time.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, almond extract and salt; mix well.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Good served warm or cold.
Can be frozen.

title: tuna cornbread casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until barely tender; drain.
Add onion, tuna, salt, pepper, soup and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Meanwhile, prepare cornbread as directed on package. Pour hot tuna mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with cornbread batter and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400° until top is golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: wok vegetables
directions: Put oil in wok and heat on high.
Put carrots in and stir until they soften.
Add cabbage.
Cook until it wilts.
Add onions, peas and chicken broth.
When cabbage is cooking in oil with carrots, cover with Mrs. Dash seasoning.

title: old-fashioned peanut candy
directions: Bring syrup to
boil; let boil about 3 minutes.
Add peanuts. Stir; add soda and stir.
Pour onto buttered dish.
You can roll in balls or let firm and cut in squares.

title: chicken 'n vegetable stir-fry(heart healthy)
directions: Thoroughly combine the first 6 ingredients.
Set aside.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet over high heat until hot.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add vegetables and soup mixture. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes or until sauce is thickened.
Stir in nuts and serve over hot rice.
Sometimes I substitute frozen French beans for the broccoli and snow peas.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add soup and pizza sauce.
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in drippings until crisp-tender.

title: best southern onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Cover bottom with half of crackers.
Add onions and cream of mushroom soup in layers until dish is full.
Cover the top with the beaten eggs; pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.

title: cheese and pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add 1/4 as much water as you have juice.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and flour.
Beat egg and add to flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add juice, water and vinegar. Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened.
Cool, but pour over cheese and pineapple while still warm.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar; let stand for 1 hour, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: applesauce spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Sift flour with soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Set aside.
In large bowl of mixer, at medium speed, cream butter with granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well and at low speed.
Beat in flour mixture. Add applesauce, walnuts and raisins.

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Defrost potatoes enough to break apart. Mix all ingredients and place in large casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: fudge crme de pot
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in the blender. Scald the milk just to the boiling point. Add to the mixture, blending for 1 minute. Pour immediately into 4 sherbet glasses and refrigerate. Top with whipped cream and serve the same day.

title: marinated crab claws
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over crab claws in bowl with airtight lid.
Refrigerate 24 hours without disturbing.
Serve as appetizer or pig out!

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash yams.
Add salt, pepper, marshmallows, cinnamon and ginger; mix well and form into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate in medium baking dish, covered.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground chuck; drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients except 3/4 cup cheese.
Spray casserole dish with Pam. Place 1/2 bag of chips in bottom of casserole dish. Pour 1/2 of ground meat mixture over chips.
Layer the rest of the chips and meat.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup cheese on top of meat.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemon supreme pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: southwestern shredded chicken salad
directions: Trim chicken breasts of visible fat. In a shallow saucepan, bring broth and cumin to a boil. Add chicken breasts and reduce heat to low. Simmer gently until chicken is done, about 10 minutes. Do not allow to boil. Remove chicken from broth and allow to cool slightly. When chicken is cool enough to handle, use 2 forks and pull with the tines of each fork in the opposite direction, shredding the chicken. Set aside.

title: punch
directions: Mix together all Jell-O's.
Add boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix and divide into 2 containers. Freeze.

title: blueberry peach jam
directions: Wash and crush fully ripe blueberries one layer at a time. Wash, peel and cut into pieces and grind the peaches.
Measure fruit into 6 or 8-quart saucepan, if necessary, add water to equal exact amount.
Measure sugar into large bowl; set aside.
Combine fruit pectin and cinnamon with fruit.
Cook over high heat until it boils, stirring constantly.
Add sugar all at once.
Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a full rolling boil (that cannot be stirred down).
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; skim and stir to remove foam.
Ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch at top.
Wipe rim of jars clean; place lids on jars and screw firmly.
Place in canner and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss chicken, celery, green pepper, onion, pimento, salt and Green Goddess dressing together lightly.
Fold in the whipped cream and cashews.
Garnish with boiled eggs.
May serve plain or in tomato cup.

title: fork cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then vanilla.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Form dough into balls; press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Reserve 1 cup and press the rest into a 9 x 13 ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: red potato salad in sour cream vinaigrette
directions: Cook potatoes until just tender.
When cool, cut in large pieces.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons vinegar and 4 tablespoons oil.
Toss lightly and set aside.

title: "fresh" green beans
directions: Wash Italian green beans under running water.
Cook two strips of bacon until crisp in saucepan, retain fat in the pan.
Add Italian green beans with coarse black pepper and finely chopped onions.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: delux pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in nuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 350° oven for 55 minutes or until done.

title: stove top barbecued spareribs
directions: Place liquids in large covered saucepan with ribs.
Bring to boil quickly, shaking pan from time to time to cover ribs with liquid.
Reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes, continuing to "swish" pan periodically.
Uncover and increase heat to high. Spoon liquid over ribs until heavy glaze remains.
Serve with rice (recommended).

title: cherries that bounce
directions: Pour off and discard 1/2 the cherry liquid.
Fill jar to top with bourbon.
Allow to age at least 3 weeks.
Drink the "bounce" happily.
Serve the cherries as cocktail nibbles.
This will keep at room temperature for a year.
The cherries get fatter and fatter.

title: red kidney bean vegetable salad
directions: Mix all together with dressing and chill well for several hours.

title: tuna noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles. Rinse with cold water when done. Drain well. Mix tuna, onion, peas and mushrooms in a large bowl. Add noodles and Miracle Whip to desired consistency. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: french fried deviled eggs (with creole sauce)
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Mash them and season with mustard, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Pack this yolk mixture back into the whites.
Put halves together and hold together with toothpicks.
Dip them into additional egg yolks which have been beaten.
Dip in flour, then in bread crumbs.
Fry in deep, hot fat (about 380°) until golden brown.
Serve with Creole Sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Pour over your favorite meat.
Bake meat slowly until very tender.
If desired, add sliced onions.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Blend sugar and coffee; add water and heat until sugar dissolves.
Add vanilla bean and bourbon.
Seal tightly.
Allow to age at least one month.
The longer, the better.
Remove bean and strain.
Keep liqueur in a tightly sealed bottle.

title: chocolate cheesecake(a company favorite)
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter.
Let stand 20 minutes, covered.
Mix sugars and eggs with oats mixture.
Sift together remaining ingredients and add to other ingredients; mix well.
Can add 1/2 cup of raisins if you want.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: frosty cranberry tip tops
directions: Crush cranberry sauce with fork; add lemon juice.
Pour into mold.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Spread over cranberry mixture.
Freeze until firm.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk together.
Add molasses.
Sift flour, salt and ginger together.
Pour into molasses mixture.
Add melted butter.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and vanilla.
Gradually blend in flour; add nuts and shape into small balls (about size of malt balls).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.
When they are still warm, place in a plastic bag with 3/4 cup powdered sugar.
Shake to coat cookies.
Remove from bag; place on wax paper to cool.
After they are completely cool, shake in powdered sugar again.
Store in tightly covered container with more powdered sugar.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen.

title: amanda's vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until done but still firm.
Drain water from vegetables.
Mix broccoli soup into vegetables
Mix the cubed Velveeta cheese with the vegetables and soup combination.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top of casserole. Bake at 300° for about 25 minutes or until crust is lightly brown.
Oven temperatures may vary.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Cook margarine and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Mix corn flake crumbs. Press evenly and firmly into a 9-inch pie pan to form crust. Chill.

title: microwave steamed clams
directions: Wash shell clams thoroughly, discarding any broken shells or open clams.
Set aside.
Pour water into 2-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave on High (100%) until water boils, 3 to 4 minutes. Add clams; cover and microwave on High (100%) until clams open, 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after half the cooking time.

title: aunt judy's chicken `n' dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and salt in 3 quarts of water. Cook until done. Remove chicken; debone and remove skin. Return chicken to broth. Take 3 cups of flour, add baking powder and cut in shortening. Add broth (hot) or milk. Stir until dough forms. Roll dough out on a floured board, fairly thin, 1/8-inch and no more than 1/4-inch. Cut into 4-inch squares and brush tops with melted butter. Drop dough into boiling broth; reduce heat to simmer and cover with lid. Cook 15 minutes without removing lid. Check; cook longer if needed. Add 1 cup milk and stir. Let sit after cooking.

title: lemon crunch
directions: Work first 3 ingredients with your hands and press into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa together.
Add enough of the milk to make a paste.
Beat in egg yolks well.
Heat remaining milk with butter and salt until butter is melted.
Add milk mixture to first mixture and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked 9-inch pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Whip the cool whip with condensed milk.
Add Kool Aid mix until blended.
Pour into pie crust.
Place in freezer 1/2 hour to set.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Brown hamburger in deep skillet.
While browning meat, heat water for macaroni.
When water boils, add macaroni.
When meat is brown begin adding tomatoes, corn and spices.
When macaroni is done, drain and add to meat.
Simmer all ingredients 10 to 20 minutes or until it is heated thoroughly.
Serves 16.

title: cookie bar
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt oleo in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over oleo.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and hot water; allow to stand and cool.
In a large mixing bowl, add eggs, sugar, butter, cocoa and oatmeal mixture.
Beat 3 minutes, then add flour, soda and salt; mix well. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Check for doneness after 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into slightly beaten egg yolks; add milk.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire.
Add 1 cup of coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Melt caramels and heavy cream.
Add rum flavoring.
Cool 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and celery with just enough water to cover until soft.
Pour off excess water and add rest of ingredients. Heat until butter is melted.

title: real german christmas cookies
directions: Chop up cherries, pecans and pineapple and mix with raisins and 1/2 cup flour.
Set aside.
Cream together butter, eggs, sugar, salt, soda and vanilla.
Blend in 3 cups of flour and fold into fruit mixture.
Then add rest of flour.
Make into 4 rolls and freeze or refrigerate.
Bake in 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: sundae ice cream
directions: In a 6-quart ice cream maker, combine condensed milk, cherries, pecans and pineapple in freezer container; stir. Add whole milk to fill line; stir. Freeze as directed.

title: peach cocktail
directions: Blend in blender to make peach nectar.
Mix 2 ounces of nectar with 6 ounces Asti Spumante.
Serve in champagne glasses.

title: orange breakfast ring
directions: Combine sugar and orange rind.
Separate biscuits; dip into oleo.
Coat with sugar.
Arrange in round cake pan or pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert on platter.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add orange juice.
Spoon over top of ring while warm.

title: mountain mud slide
directions: After all ingredients are combined, beat on high speed for 1 minute.
Bake in greased and floured 10 in. tube pan 2 hours at 300 degrees.
Cool in pan.
Don't invert.
Yields 20 pieces.

title: crusty baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Wash and drain.
Cut
in thirds lengthwise, then dip in melted butter and roll
in crumbs.
Place in greased pan and sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat in flour mixed with salt. Brown quickly in melted butter in hot skillet. Add mushrooms, onions and garlic. Cook until onions are barely tender.
Remove meat and onions from skillet. Add remaining butter to pan drippings.
When melted, blend in flour (3 tablespoons).
Add tomato paste. Slowly pour in beef stock and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Return meat, onions and mushrooms to skillet. Stir in sour cream and sherry.
Heat briefly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together and let set for 12 hours.

title: shrimp mold
directions: To Cook:
Peel shrimp.
Drain well.
Combine shrimp and cream cheese in large bowl.
Mold into ball on plate.
Top with cocktail sauce when ready to serve.
Can be refrigerated for up to 8 hours. Serve with small loaf rye bread or crackers.

title: date nut cake
directions: Let first 3 ingredients stand until cool.
Pour all in cake pan except chips and nuts.
Sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from red peppers.
Put through food chopper.
Add salt and let stand for three hours.
Drain well and add vinegar and sugar.
Simmer slowly until consistency of jam, about 1 hour. Good with kraut and potato salad.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over Cool Whip in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Let set up in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: In large roasting pan, mix popcorn and nuts.
Keep warm in 250° oven.
Butter sides of 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Combine sugar, honey and corn syrup in pan.
Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and nuts stirring to coat.
Cool. Break into small pieces.
Makes 3 quarts but won't last long!

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes. In separate pan, heat butter, soups, milk and cheese. (You may not need all the cheese, depending on how much cheese you like.) When potatoes are done, drain. Combine with cheese mixture. Mix well and serve!

title: chex chocolate mix
directions: Melt chocolate and pour over the mixture of remaining ingredients and stir through.

title: rotel dip
directions: Brown ground round, sausage and onion; drain well.
Combine in crock-pot with soup, tomatoes and cubed Velveeta.

title: chocolate-banana split pie(8 servings)
directions: In small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons chocolate syrup.
Using a fork, mix well.
Using the back of a spoon, press crumb mixture over bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate; set aside.
Using mixer on medium speed, beat frozen dessert until smooth.
Using a spatula, spread over prepared crust.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm, about 2 hours.

title: deviled cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly. Roll into 1 large ball or about 45 small balls. Roll balls in chopped nuts or chopped parsley.

title: garlic and tomato risotto(a vegetarian delight)
directions: Coat saucepan with cooking spray.
Warm over medium-high heat. Add onion.
Saute until soft but not browned.
Add 1/4 cup of broth if needed to prevent onion from browning.
Add pepper, garlic, tomatoes and spinach.
Saute, stirring for about 5 minutes.

title: homemade ravioli
directions: Place the flour on a board with a valley in the middle.
Crack 3 eggs into the valley and 2 tablespoons oil.
Add the water a little at a time while kneading.
Knead into a well-mixed ball. In a bowl mix the remaining ingredients.
Roll out the dough to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into 3-inch rounds and spoon the cheese mixture onto half.
Fold the dough and pinch edges with a spoon.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Use small cucumbers.
Use vinegar and water (half of each) and 1 tablespoon salt to each quart of liquid.

title: nana's potato salad
directions: Boil, skin and dice potatoes.
Set aside.
Make a sauce out of remaining ingredients.
Pour the mixture over the potatoes and stir.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into large mixing bowl.
Combine oleo, butter, peanut butter and water in saucepan and bring to boil; pour over sugar and flour and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients in order given and beat thoroughly.
Pour into greased cookie sheet (15 x 10-inch).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Leave cake in pan.

title: gratin of spring vegetables
directions: Trim ends of beans.
Scrape carrots and slice.
Break cauliflower into florets.
Cook vegetables separately until barely tender.
Butter a shallow, 2-quart casserole.
Arrange vegetables with carrots around outside of casserole, cauliflower in the center and green beans between them.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce, grated cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter.
Pour broth into bottom of casserole.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes, until hot and browned.
Serves 8.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese together.
Spread over cooked pie shells.

title: t.g.i.f.
directions: In skillet, saute onion in shortening until golden.
Rinse and drain the sauerkraut.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Combine with onions in skillet.
Rinse and drain potatoes.
Place potatoes in center of skillet on top of sauerkraut mixture.
Add water.
Place Kielbasa in a ring around the potatoes.
Poke kielbasa with a fork in several places to allow steam to escape.
Simmer for about 40 minutes.
Serve with crusty rye bread.

title: beef casserole
directions: Begin cooking enough noodles to cover the bottom of the baking dish.
In
a
skillet,
brown
the beef, then add salt, pepper, tomato
sauce, garlic and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Mix
the cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
In a greased baking
dish,
layer
the noodles, meat sauce, sour cream mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese and corn pie
directions: Heat corn, pepper and cheese until cheese is melted; stir in cornstarch.
Pour into pie shell; top with crust.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let sit about 5 minutes before serving.

title: black-eyed peas on new year's day for good luck
directions: Use unhusked ears of corn.
Lay back husks enough to remove silk.
Return husk to original position.
Be sure kernels aren't exposed.
Roast on grill, turning 3 or 4 times so all sides are exposed to heat.
Allow at least 30 minutes for roasting, depending on age-size of corn and proximity of heat.
When done, serve plain or season with butter.

title: fancy fancy franks
directions: Slice franks lengthwise.
Crumble onion.
Add potatoes, butter and seasonings in baking dish and blend.
Add soup and milk mixed together.
Pour 3/4 over potatoes and blend.
Arrange franks on top.
Sprinkle with onions and remaining soup.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, green pepper and onion fine.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and set aside.
Heat in microwave the remaining ingredients. Pour over slaw and refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: canned apples cold pack
directions: You will need 8 quart jars.

title: fresh haddock with sour cream dill sauce
directions: Place fillets in a baking dish and preheat oven to 350°. Spread fillets with a generous amount of sour cream.
Sprinkle with good amount of dill weed and pat liberally with butter.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Fish is done when it loses its translucent look and just begins to flake.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into uniform cubes.
Cook in boiling, salted water until done.
