Drain off water; place potatoes in refrigerator until cool.
Remove from refrigerator; stir in oil gently.
Combine sour cream and salad dressing.
Add to potatoes. Add eggs; mix gently.
Other ingredients may be added, if desired.

title: beefy cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: banana bread(easy and quick)
directions: Mix in order and bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix and sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture with sour cream or half and half.
Add vanilla.
Chill.
Roll into balls; press with glass.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Frost with butter frosting when cooled.

title: salsa spaghetti quickie
directions: Prepare spaghetti.
Squirt on margarine and toss.
Pour salsa in serving bowl.
Individuals can add their own salsa to their spaghetti and enjoy.
If making for a group, mix salsa with spaghetti before serving.
Serve immediately.
May top with garlic powder or grated Parmesan cheese.
Great with entrees or alone.

title: pink frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend cheese and undrained pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds.
Freeze overnight or until firm.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving. Unmold and garnish with more cherries.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: basic vanilla nonfat frozen yogurt
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in milk, beaten Egg Beaters and corn syrup.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in vanilla and yogurt.
Freeze in ice cream maker according to manufacturers directions.

title: potato and onion soup
directions: Cook margarine and chopped onion for 10 minutes until tender. Add flour and water, one cup at a time; stir.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat until tender.
After cooking, sprinkle in parsley.
Add sour cream when eating.
Makes 7 cups.

title: the world's best rice
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients together and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 400°.

title: coffee bars
directions: Beat the eggs. Add the coffee and brown sugar. Mix well.
Add the sifted dry ingredients. Add the oil and vanilla.
Blend well. Spread the batter on an ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle the chocolate chips and walnuts over the top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower in flowerets.
Fry bacon and crumble.
Chop onion.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill, salt, soda, egg and yeast.
Add flour to form stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85 degrees to 90 degrees) until light and doubled in size (50 to 60 minutes).
Stir dough down.
Put in a well-greased 8-inch round casserole (1-1/2 to 2 quart size).
Let rise in a warm place until light (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.
Brush with soft butter. Yield:
1 loaf.

title: diet strawberry cake
directions: Break up cake.
Put in 13 x 16-inch pan.
Put mashed berries over cake.
Boil 1 1/2 cups water.
Put in Jell-O and mix.
Mix Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.
Put more Cool Whip on top. Keep in refrigerator.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry hamburger and drain off grease. Add kidney beans and taco sauce. While this simmers, chop up tomatoes, onions, and lettuce. Crumble up bag of Doritos and line 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour a little sauce over crumbs. Sprinkle cheese over sauce (hamburger). Add a layer of tomatoes, then add lettuce to final layer. Pour buttermilk dressing over top.

title: bavanain
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Drain sauerkraut; rinse with warm water and steam for a few minutes.
Mix soup with mayonnaise; add all ingredients and put in oiled casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: locust
directions: Gather locusts at night.
Remove shells.
Do not let the sunshine hit the locust or they will spoil.
Wash and then fry them in a small amount of grease.
Serve them hot or cold.

title: crusty potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes into a bowl of cold water.
In another bowl, combine onion, egg, flour and salt.
Drain potatoes, pressing out all liquid.

title: cheese ravioli with fresh tomato and artichoke sauce
directions: Cook ravioli without salt, according to package directions. Drain well.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Toss with 1 teaspoon oil; set aside.

title: tea tassies
directions: Let cream cheese and margarine soften at room temperature, then blend and stir in flour.
Chill slightly about 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in small muffin tins.
Press dough on bottom and sides to form cup.
Makes 24 tea tassies.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Toss orange slices, apple, bananas, dates and fruit salad dressing.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add water or juice and salt; chill.
Mash soft cream cheese when Jell-O is nearly set.
Beat it, add cheese, whipped cream, pineapple and pimentos.
Put in molds or a shallow pan.
Set in cold place.
Serves 10 to 20.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop up popcorn, place in bowl.

title: banana pudding
directions: Alternate layers of vanilla wafers and sliced bananas in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: orange honey glazed ham
directions: Make diagonal cuts about 1/4 inch deep and 1 inch apart on top of ham.
Place ham on rack in shallow baking pan.
Insert a meat thermometer into center of the thickest portion of meat.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until 140°. Meanwhile, combine 2 tablespoons of the orange juice with the honey and mustard.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
After ham has cooked 1 1/4 hours, brush with 1/2 of the glaze.
Mix remaining orange juice, chicken broth and cornstarch.
Stir in remaining glaze.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly, then continue cooking for 2 minutes.
Stir in marmalade.
Pass with sliced ham.
Looks nice with warm peaches placed around ham on plate.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Melt
butter.
Beat
eggs;
add sugar.	Stir well.
Add buttermilk, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: chet's gooey wonders
directions: Melt caramels with 1/2 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, 1/4 cup evaporated milk and melted butter.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with waxed paper; press into pan half of the cake mixture and form layer the size of the pan.
Remove from pan and save for top layer. Press remaining half of cake mixture into pan and bake for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with chips and spread over with caramel mixture.
Top with other half of cake mixture.
Bake 15 minutes.
Refrigerate for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, no longer, and cut into squares.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburg, mix with taco seasonings and refried beans in frying pan. Place in casserole dish layer sour cream, salsa and monterey jack cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 min. Serve with Tortilla Chips for dipping.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain well. Add butter, milk, cheese and parsley.
Toss until fettuccine is well coated.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place in ungreased shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Place 3 slices buttered bread, cut up, on bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Set aside.
Saute fresh sliced mushrooms in butter.
Add green pepper, onion, celery, mayonnaise, mushroom soup, milk, eggs and 4 slices of bread, cut up.
Combine all ingredients together and pour in casserole over cut up buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add shredded cheese of choice and bake 10 minutes more or until cheese melts.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: wild west beans
directions: Cook combined ingredients in heavy saucepan, first bringing to a boil, then turning heat down to medium-low.
Cook about 2 hours, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
May be cooked in baking dish in a 300° oven, uncovered, for about 2 hours.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Fry out meat; save drippings.
Crumble meat and set aside. Pour fat into casserole dish.
Add peas, tomatoes, rice, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper; mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Crumble reserved meat over top and serve.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: country cornbread dressing
directions: Saute nuts, celery and onion in 1/4 cup butter.
Add to combined cornbread, bread cubes, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper; mix well.
Gradually add water, eggs and remaining 1/2 cup butter; toss lightly.
Lightly stuff dressing into 12-pound turkey.
Roast according to standard directions.
Makes 2 1/2-quarts of dressing.

title: honey pecan spinach salad
directions: In a small bowl mix mayonnaise, honey, lemon juice, and poppy seeds.
In a separate bowl toss spinach, strawberries, and grapefruit pieces.
Place sugar and chopped pecans in skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until golden brown. Break up into small pieces and set aside to cool.
Combine dressing with spinach and fruits; sprinkle pecan pieces over all. Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Prepare pan for deep frying.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out centers of potatoes, leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Fry shells a few at a time at medium heat, 2 to 3 minutes, or until golden brown.
Drain.
Place shells on cookie sheet.
Top with Velveeta cheese; broil until the cheese begins to melt.
Remove from oven and top with remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate cake and chocolate icing
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water; batter will be very thin.
Pour into greased 2 (9-inch) layer pans, 3 (8-inch) layer pans or 1 (13 x 9-inch) sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° (325° if using glass pans) for 30 to 35 minutes for layers; bake 35 to 40 minutes for sheet cake.

title: artichoke-rice salad
directions: Cook and cool rice and chicken broth.
Mix all ingredients with rice except artichoke liquid.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix artichoke liquid, 1/3 cup mayonnaise and 1/4 teaspoon curry powder.
Refrigerate overnight, then mix with rice.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions, baking in a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Boil crushed pineapple in juice and sugar for 3 minutes.
While cake is still warm, punch holes in top and slowly pour pineapple mixture over cake.
(Pour a small amount and let it soak in; continue until all syrup is used.)

title: cheese balls
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese, crumble Blue cheese, and add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix by hand with softened cream cheese. Roll in parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased casserole dish.
Put 1 slice Swiss cheese over each breast.
Mix wine and soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top of chicken.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 450°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on stove until lightly brown.
Layer 13 x 9-inch pan with wet rice.
(To 1 cup rice, add water and drain well.)
Place pork chops over rice.
Mix 1 can water with mushroom soup.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, syrup, sugar and salt together.
Boil 5 minutes. Add baking soda, mixing well.
Pour over popped corn that has been placed in a roasting pan.
Mix well.
Bake in a 250° oven for 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Combine soft drink powder and sugar.
Dissolve in milk.
Pour into soda glasses.
Add scoops of ice cream and carbonated water to fill the glass.
Stir it slightly and enjoy!

title: very easy-very good salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Gently fold in Cool Whip and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with 3/4 cup stuffing mix.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.

title: lemon pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in slow cooker.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with onion and lemon.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and drizzle on ketchup.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick rotel dip
directions: Cut cheese in large pieces; add Ro-Tel and chili.
Combine sausage.
Put in boiler and cook on low heat to melt cheese, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Fritos.

title: drumstick torte
directions: Mix wafers, peanuts and melt.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Mix milk and pudding until thick.
Spread on peanut butter mixture.
Top with Cool Whip, shaved chocolate and crushed peanuts just before serving.

title: grandma gross' chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger and finely cut onion over a slow heat.
Add tomatoes, beans and salt.
A small pinch of chili powder is okay if you like it spicier.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add a little water, if too thick.

title: tangy hot tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Pour 1 to 2 spoonfuls at a time into a cup of boiling water.

title: hamburger pie casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; pour into casserole.
Add soup to drained beans and heat.
Pour over hamburger.
Mash potatoes, add milk, egg and seasoning.
Spoon over beans.
Dab well with butter or margarine.

title: "jiffy" steamed syrup pudding
directions: Put bread crumbs in an enormous bowl, add fruit and nuts and mix well with fingers so that each piece is coated with the crumbs. Sprinkle next 4 ingredients over all.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1/2 of the soup, mashed potatoes and cheese).
Press firmly into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Frost with mashed potatoes; top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until done.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: Combine flour and baking soda in a large bowl.
Combine milk and mayonnaise; stir in ham and cheese.
Add this mixture to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 16 to 18 minutes. Yields 1 dozen.

title: grand meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili sauce (may substitute tomato sauce).
Shape into loaf.
Pour chili sauce over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good hot or cold.
Makes good sandwiches.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats, water and margarine; let stand for 20 minutes. Cream sugar and eggs. Add oat mixture and dry ingredients. Mix well. Turn into greased, floured oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: orange punch
directions: Mix ginger ale and pineapple juice in punch bowl.
Spoon orange sherbet into juice mixture.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup, mayo, milk, cheese, juice and curry together.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs together.
Put first mixture over broccoli in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Put chicken on top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over and push down.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dieters' watergate lite salad
directions: In a bowl, combine pudding and pineapple, juice included.
Mix until pudding is dissolved.
Add whipped topping and mix altogether.
Next, fold in 1/2 cup pecans and marshmallows.
Pour mixture into glass dish and top with remaining 1/2 cup chopped pecans and dot with cherries.
Refrigerate for 3 hours before serving.

title: meatless minestrone
directions: Place herbs into cheesecloth.
Add to rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Remove cheesecloth.
Serve hot.
Yields 25 to 30 servings.

title: chile
directions: Brown ground beef, using seasoning salt in moderation. Put all other ingredients in a crock-pot and turn heat to high.
Add ground beef and stir occasionally.

title: fruity cheese cupcakes
directions: Put cupcake papers in cupcake pans.
Place one vanilla wafer in each paper, round side down.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix very well.
Fill cupcake papers a little more than full with mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Place 1 tablespoon of cherry pie filling in the middle of each cupcake.
"You may also use blueberry or strawberry pie filling."
Yields 20 to 24 tarts.

title: golden glow cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk.
Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 1 (13 x 9-inch) cake.

title: inside out chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a bundt pan that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Dump out of pan while hot.

title: jalapeno cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in either a crock-pot or top of a double boiler or fondue pan.
Heat on low until cheese is creamy.
Use your favorite chips to dip.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. This recipe can be doubled. Tastes even better if made a day in advance.

title: scrod with onions
directions: Lightly coat large skillet with spray.
Over medium-high heat, add onion, 1/2 of soy sauce and dash of pepper sauce.
Cover; cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add water and fish. Sprinkle with rest of soy sauce and another dash of Tabasco. Cover; simmer until fish flakes easily, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: black magic cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift all dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Add eggs and liquids; stir until batter is smooth. (Batter will be thin.)
Pour into well-greased a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.
Top with buttercream frosting or one of your favorite frostings.

title: reduced sodium stir-fry
directions: Saute onions in margarine in a wok or skillet.
Remove from pan; add oil and heat until pan is hot enough that one vegetable dropped in oil sizzles.
Add meat, stirring until brown.
Add vegetables, combine broth, soy sauce and sugar.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Cover pan and cook just until vegetables are tender-crisp.
To thicken stir-fry, add 1 tablespoon cornstarch to 2 tablespoons cold chicken broth or water.
Serve over rice.
Makes five 1-cup servings 151 calories; 281 mg. sodium per serving.

title: pink punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill in refrigerator until ready to serve. Makes 1 gallon.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs and oil and mix well. Add apples; mix well and add nuts. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients together and chill. Keeps 4 to 5 days in refrigerator.

title: maja blanco
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the cream-style corn, evaporated milk, 1 can coconut milk and sugar.
Add 10 or more drops of yellow food coloring.
Mix thoroughly in a bowl, 1 can coconut milk and 1 cup cornstarch.
When smooth and no lumps are left, pour into boiling mixture.
Stir constantly at medium fire until desired consistency. (Thick enough that the mixture sticks to the mixing spoon.)
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Spread pecans over bottom layer.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Pour over bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl delight
directions: Combine water and sugar in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemonade, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Turn into large container.
Stir in Hawaiian Punch.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Pour mixture into punch bowl and add ginger ale.
Serves 35 to 40.

title: spinach salad with celery seed dressing
directions: Place almonds on cookie sheet and spread out evenly.
Toast in oven about 10 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Set aside.

In large bowl, tear up enough spinach to serve one person (about a handful); top with 3 slices bacon, broken into pieces, 1 green onion, thinly sliced, 2 mushrooms, thinly sliced, 1 hard-boiled egg, finely chopped (I use the cheese grater right over the bowl) and a sprinkle of toasted slivered almonds.
Continue this layering three more times or until all ingredients are used up. Top with mandarin oranges and refrigerate until ready to serve, then toss with desired amount of Celery Seed Dressing.

title: ham and cheese power squares
directions: Combine potatoes with turkey ham, cheese, eggs, yogurt, salt and pepper. Spread evenly in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown and center is firm.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting in serving squares. Garnish with apple slices and serve immediately.
Makes 12 servings.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Shape into oval patties.
Cook in pan until brown through.
Add gravy, water and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes or so.

title: shrimp gumbo(grand isle)
directions: Peel uncooked shrimp.
Refrigerate.
Make roux (dark) of flour and 2 tablespoons oil.
To make roux you must cook slowly and stir constantly.
It must be the color of chocolate when finished.
Set aside.

title: buenlos
directions: Beat eggs; add cream and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and combine with liquid.
Dough should be soft and easy to roll.
Add more flour if needed.
Let stand for two hours.
Turn out on floured board and roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into desired shapes and deep fry until nicely browned.
Sprinkle with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.

title: creamy italian toss(one dish salad meal)
directions: Prepare spaghetti as desired.
Drain.
In small bowl, stir together next 5 ingredients.
Set aside.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix last three ingredients together.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6. Good served with brown rice.

title: holiday breakfast pizza
directions: Cook crumbled sausage until browned; drain fat.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and sides to form crust.
Spoon cooked sausage over crust.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and then shake. You will have your own sauce for hamburgers and even French fries.

title: crisp peanut candies
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat chips and peanut butter over low heat until melted. Stir until smooth. Add cereal and peanuts. Stir to coat. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let stand until set. Store in an airtight container at room temperature. Yield: about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and beat mixture with beater until crumbly.
Take half of the mixture and press evenly to the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peach pie filling on top of crust and spread evenly.
Spread remaining mixture on top of filling.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Heat until hot the Monterey Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, green chilies, onions, cheese soup and chicken soup.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine 7-Up, ginger ale and juices.
Add sherbet and ice cream into punch.
Stir.
Serve immediately.

title: peach or strawberry delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine first 3 ingredients and spread in Pyrex 9 x 13-inch or two 9 x 9-inch aluminum pans.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook diced potatoes and carrots.
Cool.
Add onion, which has been cut into rings and diced eggs.
Marinate with dressing of vinegar, salad oil, salt, sugar and mustard.
Add mayonnaise.
Mix gently.
Chill.
Flavors blend well when prepared the night before.

title: welsh scones
directions: Beat egg with enough milk to equal 2/3 cup.
Add to sifted dry ingredients, then add currants.
Add Crisco.
Mix thoroughly. Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Enjoy with tea!
Makes 12 scones.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the squash and onion together until tender.
Drain off the excess water.
Combine squash, cheese, soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick spicy chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, honey, jalapeno pepper, hot pepper sauce, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper.
Arrange chicken over lettuce, top with tomatoes and mushrooms.
Drizzle with dressing mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jane's corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and mix.
Add all other ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Butter baking dish.
Pour half of mixture in and cover with cracker crumbs.
Repeat.
Dot top with butter and bake in covered dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil until soft ball stage, about 30 minutes.
Pour over popcorn and stir it to cover all of the corn.
Keep in plastic wrap.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix in mixer, cheese, cream, sugar and coloring.
Whip.
Drain all fruit and fold in with marshmallows, etc.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: coffee cake(biscuits)
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Melt margarine.
Mix sugars, cinnamon and nuts.
Dip each biscuit in butter; roll in sugar mix.
Stack on edges in pan.
Pour remaining butter and sugar mix over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set in pan for 5 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: fruit dunkers
directions: *Dip these fruits in lemon juice immediately after cutting to prevent discoloration.

title: surprise brownie cupcakes
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs and gradually add 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Add 1 stick margarine. Blend well.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Add pecans and coconut, if desired.
Drop by about 3 tablespoonfuls into paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 cupcakes.

title: miss ruby's heath bars
directions: Line 9x15 inch cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with a layer of saltine crackers.
Boil sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top and smooth with a spoon until melted.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: montecados(spanish cookies)
directions: Preheat the oven to 250°.
Combine the flour, sugar and cinnamon together.
Add the melted shortening until all is mixed in well.
Stir in the anise and knead for 5 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Place a blanched almond on top of each cookie and push down slightly. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
You do not want to brown the cookies. They should remain pale.
Let cookies cool on cookie sheet for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all, except onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Add onion rings the last 10 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in a tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Timing could depend on the actual oven temperature.)
Invert onto a round flat plate.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Add sour milk mixture.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Roll out on floured board and cut out with a biscuit cutter.
Put filling on one cookie, then cover with another.
Seal edges.

title: dieter's salad dressing
directions: Toss salad well. Top with dressing.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in a large heavy saucepan over moderate heat.
Add the onions and cook, stirring occasionally, for about 5 minutes until they are soft but not browned.
Add the carrots, chicken stock and rice. Simmer gently, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Put the soup through a sieve or food mill into a clean saucepan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and stir in the cream.
If it looks too pale, add the tomato paste.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl and stir until blended.
Grease 2 (9-inch) pie plates.
Divide mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 6 pieces.
Combine the flour and salt; pound 2 tablespoons into meat.
Brown on both sides, transfer to baking dish.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour mixture into pan drippings.
Stir in drained tomatoes, celery, carrots and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: bean dip
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, combine all ingredients until well blended.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly. Serve immediately with tortilla chips.

title: 1939 cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello and mix well. Whip Milnot milk; fold whipped Milnot into jello mixture.

title: spinach casserole
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan make 3 to 4 rows of Ritz.
Combine spinach and cheese.
Sprinkle over Ritz.
In bowl mix all other ingredients.
Pour over crackers.
Crush 5 to 6 Ritz and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: filhos(portuguese donuts)
directions: Scald milk with butter and lemon rind.
Remove from heat. Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Let cool.
Put in 2 eggs at a time and mix well after each egg addition.
Heat oil to donut degree on thermometer.
Drop batter by teaspoon in hot oil. Deep fry until brown. Turn if necessary. Remove with slotted spoon and dip in powdered sugar.

title: pickle relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, cabbage, onion, mangoes and salt.
Cover with cracked ice for 3 hours.
Drain and add sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add green coloring.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak, onion and celery in 2 tablespoons hot fat.
Add pepper, sugar, water and bouillon cube.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add green pepper and simmer 5 to 10 minutes more.
Add cornstarch.
Serve over rice or Chinese noodles.
Add more water if desired.

title: creole chocolate cake
directions: Pour coffee over chocolate.
Cool.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cloves.
Add shortening, cooled chocolate mixture, milk and vanilla.
Beat two minutes with electric mixer on medium speed.
Add eggs and beat two more minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with White Mountain Icing.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. Slowly fold in dressing and chips.

title: sweetheart punch
directions: Add ginger ale and ice cream when serving.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Coat chicken breasts with mayonnaise on both sides.
Roll in grated cheese until coated well.
Place in slightly greased pan. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Turn over once after 1/2 hour.

title: pink cloud
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple and sugar. Add Jell-O. Let cool. Add cottage cheese, pecans and Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: holiday clay-time ornaments and objects
directions: Mix salt, water and flour.
Press dough into flat shapes and place on baking sheet.
Put holes at the tops for hanging on your tree.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 275° until brown.
Cool and paint them.
Add shellac or varnish.
Hang on Christmas tree with yarn.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix all other ingredients, one at a time, mixing after each addition.
Cook at 325° in 2 oblong pans for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: elberta's japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat egg yolks; add raisins, nuts and coconut.
Add milk and flour, which have been sifted with spices and salt.
Beat egg whites; fold into mixture and bake in 4 layers at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cold slaw
directions: Put all ingredients, except cabbage and vinegar in pan.
When boiled, add vinegar.
Stir well and pour over the cabbage.

title: melt-in-your mouth wedding cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and confectioners sugar together in a bowl.
Add vanilla and water; stir.
Gradually mix in flour and pecans; stir together until completely blended.
Roll dough into small individual balls and flatten slightly.
Put in a greased cookie pan and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until slightly brown.
Then roll in powdered sugar when cool enough to handle.

title: twinkie cake
directions: *I add 1 to 2 cups fresh strawberries when in season.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Mix and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and form into balls. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until golden brown.

title: lazy man's cabbage rolls
directions: Place cabbage in greased casserole.
Saute beef and onion lightly; add rice and soup.
Pour beef mixture over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese until light.
Add sugar, gradually beating constantly.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add cream cheese mixture; beat well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: diabetic pineapple-orange marmalade
directions: Drain juice from pineapple into saucepan; sprinkle gelatin on juice.
Wait 1 minute, until it is soft, then heat gently, until gelatin melts.
Remove from heat and stir in crushed pineapple, thawed orange juice and orange jello with NutraSweet.
Store in covered jars in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti
directions: Meatballs: Roll out the meat into a ball.
Put it in a pan and cook it.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cooked.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Serve with raw vegetables or crackers.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: puppy chow(microwave)
directions: Stir chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine together. Put in microwave for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Gently stir in Rice Chex.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice Jonathan apples to fill dish.
Sprinkle over a bit of flour, 3/4 cup sugar and sprinkle cinnamon over apples. May dot with butter (optional).
Cover with top crust.
Make slits and sprinkle sugar over crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: sweet potato-cashew bake
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces and cook until just tender.
Drain and place in a shallow, 2-quart casserole.

title: whiskey balls
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Roll balls in confectioners sugar.
Store in sealed container.
Improves with age.

title: mighty minestrone soup
directions: In large casserole, heat the oil until hot. Stir in the cabbage and onions, and saut them over medium-high heat until the cabbage is wilted, about 8-10 minutes.

title: diabetic moist fruit cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in margarine, vanilla and sweetener.
Stir in rest of ingredients and combine well.
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie down slightly.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Do not overbake or cookies will be dry.
Store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks.
Yields 20 cookies.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix well, oleo, water, eggs, oil and 1/2 can milk.
Add to cake mix, blend well.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt caramels and add rest of can of milk, saving back 6 tablespoons for frosting.
Pour caramel and milk mixture over baked layer; sprinkle with pecans.
Pour rest of batter on top and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend	eggs,
sugar,
shortening
and	peanut	butter. Alternately
add
milk
and flour.	Roll into 1-inch balls and flatten with tines of a fork.
Moisten fork with water between each cookie
to
keep
it
from sticking.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes on ungreased baking pan.

title: our punch
directions: Mix prechilled ingredients just before serving.
Add food coloring.

title: no cook fruit cake
directions: Dice all fruit and crush vanilla wafers.
Mix together.
Add all other ingredients, then press into a buttered dish and keep refrigerated.

title: "sunshine cake"
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored, then wash and thoroughly dry the beaters.
Don't have a speck of egg yolk in the white or they are apt not to beat stiff.
Beat egg whites until they form peaks, then add cream of tartar.
Make a syrup with the sugar and water.
Cook the syrup until it spins a hair.
Beating the egg whites on high speed pour the hot syrup into the egg whites in a very fine stream.
Reduce the speed to as slow as possible and add the beaten egg yolks (slowly), then add the vanilla.
Sift the flour and salt together and add, beating as little as possible. Bake in ungreased tube pan for one hour at 325°.
Remove from oven, invert pan for one hour on a cake rack.
It is good with a marshmallow icing or just a glaze.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except lemon juice, together and chill for a couple of hours.
Sprinkle lemon juice over top of dip and mix in.
Serve with Town House crackers or crackers of choice.

title: cheese ball i
directions: Mix both cheeses well. Roll into a ball, then roll in chopped nuts. Chill for a couple of hours. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Crush crackers; set aside.
In 1-quart casserole dish, beat eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Add 3/4 of crackers to casserole dish.
Now add corn; mix well.
Melt margarine and mix with rest of crackers.
Sprinkle over corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Spread in casserole, shredded cabbage.	Cover with meat mixture (hamburg, onion, pepper, salt and potatoes).
Top with three
more
cups
of shredded cabbage.
Pour tomato soup over top.
Bake,
covered,
at 350° for one hour or more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Add Jell-O to applesauce; heat until melted.
Add orange juice, then add 7-Up.
Stir.
Put in a mold.
Put in refrigerator. Grated carrots and celery can be added.
It's good anyway.

title: saucy little meat loaves
directions: Combine ingredients and shape into 6 individual meat loaves. Place in shallow baking pan.

title: texas corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat muffin pan before spooning mixture in.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls (buckeyes)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips and wax.
Pat into balls (approximately 1/2-inch in diameter).
Do not roll.
Shave wax into chocolate chips while melting in double boiler.
Drop balls in chocolate mixture.
Coat on all sides.
Place on wax paper.
Refrigerate a few minutes, if necessary.
Store in airtight container.
Makes approximately 40 to 50 cookies.

title: corn and cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then bake uncovered until knife comes out clean.

title: zesty meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into a loaf (8 x 4 x
1 1/2-inches).
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for
hour.
Let meat loaf stand 5 minutes before slicing. Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake eggs, sugar, add pecans and all ingredients.
Stir well. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 325 degrees for 50 minutes until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water in small bowl.
In large bowl combine 1/4 cup sugar, oil and hot water.
Add 1/2 cup flour and egg.
Mix in yeast mixture and enough self-rising flour (about 4 cups) to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and let rest 10 to 15 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Put into oiled bowl and turn over so top is oiled.
Let rise until double in size.
Turn out on floured surface, knead until smooth and roll out very thin.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Spread cinnamon mixture on dough.
Take oleo, pinch in small pieces and spread over sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Roll into a tight tube.
Cut crossways into 1/2-inch slices and place cut side up in an oiled pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven until brown. Glaze with powdered sugar glaze while still warm.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in a large bowl on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir until all the chocolate has melted and is smooth.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk; blend well.
Refrigerate until the mixture has cooled, probably about 10 minutes.
Fold in prepared whipped topping and blend until smooth.
Spoon mixture into crust and freeze about 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with chocolate curls.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Place in 8 x 4-inch pan.
Cover top of loaf with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat; drain if necessary.
Put McCormick mix into meat; stir.
Put spaghetti sauce into meat; rinse bottle with water and add to meat.
Boil lasagna noodles in water with a tablespoon olive oil; drain when tender.

title: first snow hash
directions: Simmer ham with enough water to cover for 4 hours.
Add turnips, onions, carrots and potatoes; simmer in broth until done. Add cabbage last.
It takes less time to cook cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice ham.
Surround with vegetables.
Thicken juice and pour over all.
Serve with biscuits.

title: flour tortillas
directions: In
a large mixing bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder; stir well.
With a pastry blender, cut in Crisco until mixture
resembles
coarse meal.
Gradually stir in hot water, mixing well.
Make 24 (1 1/2-inch) balls;
roll each ball on a floured
surface
to
a
6-inch circle.
Cook over medium-high heat
in
an ungreased skillet about 2 minutes on each side or until
lightly
browned.
Pat tortillas lightly with a spatula while
browning
the second side, if they puff up during cooking. Serve
hot.
Store
in refrigerator for 5 days or freeze any that is left.

title: blueberry oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: In medium glass bowl, combine all ingredients.
Heat 5 minutes on High, stirring once.
Continue cooking on power level 5 an additional 8 to 10 minutes until sauce is slightly thickened, stirring twice.
Use as a basting sauce on chicken, ribs, hamburgers, etc.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss all together using favorite salad dressing.

title: peanut butter and jello bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Reserve 1 cup of dough.
Press remaining dough in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with jelly.
Crumble reserved dough and sprinkle over jelly.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Cool and drizzle with glaze.
Cut into 2 x 1/2-inch bars.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream together margarine, eggs, brown sugar and peanut butter; add flour and baking powder.
Grease or spray with Pam a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oriental salad
directions: Combine nappa cabbage, mushrooms, green onions and water chestnuts.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and pumpkin; add flour, soda and cinnamon. Spray Pam on cookie sheet.
Put wax paper on sheet and spray lightly.
Spread mixture and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll ball in crushed pecans.

title: ice cream
directions: For this recipe, you will need the large green bananas called, Plaintains, not regular yellow bananas.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken, then shred and place in casserole dish.
Mix soups and milk; heat.
Pour over chicken.
Spread stuffing mix evenly over chicken.
Melt oleo and pour over stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meal in a dish
directions: Saute
onion and green pepper in oil.
Add other ingredients except cheese.
Place in casserole dish and cover with grated cheese and bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Beat eggs separately.
Add half of sugar to each.
To the yellows, add graham crackers and nuts.
Fold in white mixture. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool; cut in squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on meat and keep spreading.

title: pork chops and cabbage
directions: Broil pork chops. In saucepan, place quartered cabbage (remove center). Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 45 minutes. Turn in pork chops and cook for 15 minutes more.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: carrot-tuna salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in salad bowl; season.
Mix milk and mayonnaise; whip together with fork.
Mix into salad mixture, tossing with fork until well blended.
Cover bowl and allow to stand in refrigerator until ready to serve.
At the last minute, add can of shoestring potatoes.
Mix.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Serves 6.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over pretzels, mixing well.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Store covered.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix and pour into three 9-inch pie shells, uncooked.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 3 pies.

title: chicken dudley
directions: Chicken may be skinned and boned.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish after combining jelly, dressing and soup mix in a large bowl, mixing well and coating chicken on all sides.
Bake chicken for 45 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Mix eggs, corn and milk.
Blend all ingredients together.
Add green pepper and onions.
Pour mixture into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until dry when tested.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat the egg; add the milk.
Sift the salt, sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Add the eggs and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter into funnel, holding finger over the bottom. Allow batter to run out of funnel into deep fat at 375°, making swirls in fat from center out.
Cakes may be made to size wanted. Fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper.
Serve with powdered sugar.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch bits with butter over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs with sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder; beat until blended.
Add melted butterscotch mixture, then stir in nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares or bars.
Yield:
about 50 brownies.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine jello with pineapple until moistened.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Cut up half can of orange sections and add to delight mixture. Garnish with remaining orange sections. Coconut or nuts may be added.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook chicken in 2 tablespoons butter until tender in skillet or wok.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce, mushrooms, season packet from noodles until tender.
Boil noodles until tender, drain.
Add to chicken mixture.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Chow mein is now done.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise; blend until smooth.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: brussels sprouts in onion cream
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts in steamer for 15 minutes or until tender.
Saute onion in butter until rich brown.
Stir in sour cream and heat, stirring constantly.
Add Brussels sprouts and mix well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: salmon loaf with shrimp sauce
directions: Drain salmon, saving liquid.
Flake salmon into bowl; add onion, parsley, lemon juice, seasonings and oatmeal; mix lightly. Add salmon liquid plus enough milk to make 1 cup; add eggs and melted butter.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into greased 2-quart loaf pan or casserole (I use Pam).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until loaf is set in center.
Spoon shrimp sauce over top. Makes 8 servings.
This recipe may be halved for smaller loaf.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft.
Cover with water.
Add other ingredients and simmer for at least 2 hours.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Cream powdered sugar, cream cheese, pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip until smooth.
Layer cookies and filling in small bucket or clay pot.
Top layer should be cookies.
Serve with garden shovel.
Put silk flowers in center for decorations.

title: nut bread
directions: Put in flat pan in warm place.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Use 4 to 5 medium stalks of celery; scrape strings.
Combine cheese, margarine, Worcestershire and celery leaves.
Fill celery, using 2-inch pieces.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Add water to make 3 cups liquid.
Add juice to 2 packages of pudding mix.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add bananas and cherries.
Chill before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix the shortening and sugar.
Stir in beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients several times.
Mix in with banana mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot ham 'n cola
directions: Thoroughly combine brown sugar, mustard and horseradish. Moisten with just enough cola to make a smooth paste.
Reserve, remaining cola.
Rub entire ham with mixture.
Place ham in crock-pot and add remaining cola.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 10 hours (on high for 2 to 3 hours).

title: clara's chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add flour, cocoa, soda and baking powder.
Add vanilla and cold water last. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, place 1/2 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Place cauliflower flowerets; cover.
Cook on Full power 5 minutes.
Top with crumb mixture and heat on Medium power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.

title: old-fashioned dark fruitcake
directions: Mix fruits together in a large bowl; add the molasses and wine and let stand overnight.
Cream the shortening; gradually add sugar, then beat in eggs, mixing well after each addition.
Add to fruit and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 medium or 4 small loaf pans which have been greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake at 275° for about 2 1/2 hours with a pan of water on oven floor or lower rack.
Remove from pans to cool, but leave wax paper on cake.

title: poor man's fruitcake
directions: Mix brown sugar, water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves in a saucepan and boil for 3 minutes.
Cool, then add soda, salt and 2 teaspoons of water.
Sift together flour and baking powder and blend into mixture.
Bake at 325° in square pan for 55 minutes or in loaf pan for 75 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Spread butter on a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together eggs, flour, milk, salt, baking powder, cheese and spinach.
Put into pan.
Cook for 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly and cut into little squares.
Reheat at 325° for 6 to 8 minutes if squares are at room temperature or 12 to 15 minutes if squares are frozen.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add cooking oil.
Ad buttermilk and yeast.
Mix well.
Place desired amount of dough on floured cloth.
Pat out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Let warm to room temperture before baking in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be mixed, rolled, cut and placed in oven immediately if desired or may be taken from refrigerator, spooned into muffin pan (greased) and placed immediately in oven without being allowed to rise.
Mixture can be stored in covered bowl in refrigerator for a week and used as needed.

title: dark devil's food cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add the shortening.
Pour in over half of the water and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add remaining water and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) for 30 to 40 minutes for layers or 35 to 40 minutes for oblong.
Good for picnics; doesn't crumble.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Cover beans with water; soak overnight.
Drain and rinse beans.
Put in large kettle with 3 quarts of water; bring to boil and simmer gently for 1 hour, covered.
Add cabbage, carrots, turnips and canned tomatoes; cover and continue simmering 1/2 hour longer.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine ingredients in large casserole dish. Bake 1 hour at 375°, stirring once when butter has thoroughly melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Salt and pepper to your taste.
Put in baking dish, cover with grated cheese.
Mix cream of mushroom soup and evaporated milk together. Pour over cheese and broccoli.
Cover with frozen French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° or 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: First, crush cookies in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Second, combine butter, Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Use part of it to layer over cookies.
Third, combine pudding, milk and vanilla; blend until thickened.
Add part of this to previous layer.
Continue to layer, leaving some crumbs for the top. Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash, zucchini and onion in small amount of water, with sugar and salt until tender.
Drain.
Add butter and mash well.
Season with salt and pepper.
In a deep 2 quart casserole make 4 layers of vegetable and mixed cheese ending with cheese layer.
Combine milk and cream and pour over all.
Sprinkle more cheese on top, if desired.
Bake 300 for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: eggless crazy cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt together. Add the oil, water, vinegar and vanilla. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or more in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and set aside. Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon seasoned salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onion rings.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange chops on top. Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Top with rest of cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: fanny's brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup of evaporated milk.
While melting, mix in large bowl cake mix, melted butter, pecans and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Put 1/2 this mixture in buttered and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not spread; break apart with fingers. Bake 6 minutes at 350° (no longer).
Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips and caramel mixture.
Spoon rest of cake mixture over top.
(Do not spread.)
Return to oven and bake additional 16 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: dorothy's potatoes and beans
directions: In a pot, saute the onions and celery in a small amount of oil. Add seasonings.
Simmer 5 minutes. Add raw potatoes.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Cover and boil until potatoes are tender. Drain beans and add to pot. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
(If too dry, add juice from beans.)

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil Karo syrup, butter, salt and brown sugar to 240° or until rolls in ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add soda; beat well.
Pour over popcorn gradually and stir until completely coated.
Place in a 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool, then store in airtight bags or containers.

title: first bank peanut krispies
directions: Mix
together	margarine,
peanut
butter
and
Rice Krispies.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate bar over hot water.
Dip balls into chocolate until covered.
Place
on waxed paper and cool. Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: apple pie(10-inch)
directions: If apples are not tart, add 1 tablespoon lemon juice.

title: baked tomato halves
directions: Wash tomatoes, remove stems.
Cut in half crosswise.
Place cut sides up in shallow baking pan.
In 2 tablespoons butter saute onion until tender.
Stir in mustard and Worcestershire.
Spread on tomatoes.
Melt remaining butter.
Add bread crumbs and parsley.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes or until heated through and crumbs are golden brown at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Form a crust on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter and graham crackers.
Layer other ingredients over crust (spread walnuts over top and press in with hand).
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease large baking dish.
Put layer of dressing mix.
Add layer of chicken, layer onions and celery; cover with chicken soup.
Add rest of stuffing mix.
Cut up 1 stick of margarine over top.
Pour chicken broth over top and bake at 350° until brown.

title: blueberry-peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash blueberries and set aside to drain.
In a medium bowl combine dry muffin mix, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut in butter; then stir in nuts.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Soak stale French bread cubes in milk.
Melt butter and add sugar, eggs, vanilla and raisins.
Mix all together with hands. Bake in greased and buttered 8-inch baking pan about 45 minutes at 350°.
If desired, serve with Hard Sauce and a dollop of whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: becky's favorite fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and boil to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla.
Cool in cold water until it starts to thicken.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: texas panhandle cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage; place in large bowl.
Add chopped green onions with some tops.
Add Ramen noodles (uncooked), broken into small pieces.
Toast almonds and sesame seed in about a tablespoon of butter or margarine.
Cool nuts and seed before adding to the salad mixture, then toss well to mix.

title: new england cornbread
directions: Mix the sugar, flour, cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Add the eggs, 1 cup milk and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake in a greased pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: wash day cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa and baking powder.
Add the milk, melted butter, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Add Topping to cake.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all.
Bake in a 350° oven until firm.
Presto, your cake is already iced!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: curried pork chops
directions: Combine butter and curry powder in a skillet.
Saute pork chops over medium heat until done.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and parsley.
Pour beer over chops and place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips.
Add sugar and beaten eggs. Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: erna's caramel frosting
directions: Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil briskly for 1 minute.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, egg yolks, flour and milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Place in baked pastry shell; top with meringue and brown.

title: pumpkin pie(sugar-free)
directions: Beat eggs and add in order:
spices, salt, sweetener, melted butter, hot pumpkin and scalded milk.
Pour into pastry shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "cowboy" cookies
directions: Sift together and set aside.
Flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Slowly add flour mixture and mix well.
Add oats, vanilla, fold in chocolate bits.
Dough is crumbly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes. Makes a lot!

title: taco bean dip
directions: In a small bowl mix all ingredients except cheese.
Put mixture in a pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts.

title: pineapple delight
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix jello, boiling water and pineapple juice.
Add cream cheese; mix until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Make Dream Whip according to package directions.
Add partly set jello to Dream Whip.
Add mandarin oranges.
Let stand until set.

title: onion bread twist
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast from hot roll mix in water. Stir in cheese, onion, oil, mustard and egg. Add flour mixture. Blend well. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 45 to 60 minutes. Grease (not oil) cookie sheet.
On well floured surface, toss dough until no longer sticky. Divide dough into 2 pieces.
Shape each into a 12-inch long roll.
On greased cookie sheet, twist the 2 rolls together 3 times; seal ends.
Beat water with egg white; brush over loaf.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 30 to 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Scoop out yolks and chop up in a bowl.
Mix mustard and vinegar with yolk.
Mix enough mayonnaise to make a paste out of yolk mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste. Fill egg white halves with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: shrimp pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Saute zucchini until lightly brown. Add mushrooms and beans.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Saute onion. Remove vegetables.
Add shrimp, sauteed onion, lemon juice, salt and seasoning.
Add pasta and dressing.
Toss gently and refrigerate until chilled.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Grease loaf pans and line with waxed paper.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 300°, until almost done.
Turn oven off and let bread stand in oven for 1 hour.
Wrap and keep in refrigerator.
Yields 3 medium loaves.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square pan with foil.
Butter foil; set aside. In heavy 4-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and salt; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a rolling boil.
Boil without stirring until syrup when dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool at room temperature of 110° (lukewarm).
Beat with wooden spoon until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Spread in to prepared pan. Cool.
Cut into squares.
About 36 pieces or 1 3/4 pounds.

title: currant squares
directions: Make pie crust to fit cookie sheet (11 x 16-inch).
Use one box for bottom; save one for top.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix butter, oil, sugar and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add sour cream, vanilla and zucchini; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix good with electric mixer.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy enchiladas(easy and fun!  these taste great and are low-fat!)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray. Also spray large skillet.
Heat and add bell peppers, onion and cilantro.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in beans.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Melt
margarine
and
marshmallows in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and food coloring and stir until well blended.
Fold in cornflakes.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto
waxed
paper-lined
cookie sheets, shaping into
2-inch wreaths.
Decorate each with red candies.
Do not freeze.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk, eggs, salt, onion and cheese together. Add to broccoli (drained). Mix together. Pour in greased (or sprayed with Pam) pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: quick and easy nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, onion powder and minced garlic, if desired.
Combine beef, salsa, beans, sour cream and 2 cups cheese in slow cooker.
Cover.
Heat on low 2 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle with 1 cup shredded cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.
Yield: 10 to 15 servings.

title: pineapple-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together, then fold in the whipped topping.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of butter until smooth.
Add chopped onion, chicken, salt, pepper and milk.
Separate crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Pat out seams.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto crescent rolls.
Seal edges completely.
Place sealed side on baking sheet.
Brush with butter.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 125 year old black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings and beat.
Add combined flour and baking powder alternately with milk, ending with flour.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes or so and remove from pan.

title: company carrots
directions: Steam carrots until still crisp; drain well and add pineapple and juice, raisins, Grande Marnier; simmer until hot.
Add a little brown sugar if preferred.
Serves 4.

title: glazed chicken breast
directions: In a small bowl, thoroughly combine onion soup mix, preserves and water.
Set aside.
Take an aluminum foil-lined broiler pan and arrange chicken breasts and the peppers and pour soup mixture over top.
Broil 10 minutes or until chicken is done, turning one time.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: everything onions
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet. When it begins to turn brown, add sugar and mix well. Add onion and simmer (low) for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add beef broth. In a small bowl, combine cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Stir into onion mixture and cook until slightly thickened. Serve over meat, noodles or rice.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together and make small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sundae cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, cocoa, and water.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Place marshmallows evenly on top.
Make cake batter following package directions.
Pour into pan; top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, cut into squares to serve.

title: meatball mac
directions: Fry hamburger, egg, onion, bread crumbs, salt, thyme and pepper. Drain fat. Add other ingredients; bring to a boil and add 8 ounces spaghetti noodles, broken up into 1/2-inch pieces. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: bunny patch dessert
directions: Line bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish with cake slices. Top with pie filling and all of the whipped topping. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until ready to serve. Tint coconut pale green with food coloring. Sprinkle over center of whipped topping. Decorate with Easter candies and decorations like marshmallow bunnies and jelly beans.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; put in 13 x 9 pan.
Place sliced bananas on top of crust.
Beat cream cheese, then beat in milk. Add pudding; beat until well blended.
Spread over banana slices. Spoon pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread whipped cream over pudding mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: bisque of butternut squash and apple
directions: Combine stock, squash, apples, onions, sugar, salt, rosemary and pepper in heavy large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until squash is tender.
Puree squash mixture in blender or processor until smooth.
Return to pot and bring to a boil.
Melt butter in another heavy large saucepan over med. low heat.
Whisk in flour and cook 3 minutes.
Whisk in squash puree.
Simmer 3- 5 minutes.
Mix in sherry.
Beat egg yolks and cream in a small bowl. Blend in some of the hot soup into egg mixture to temper, then mix back into soup.
Rewarm if necessary.
Do not boil.

title: barbecue chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil in large skillet.
Stir in barbecue sauce and water.
Cover and cook over medium to low heat for 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in rice and corn.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lacy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet(s) with foil.
Mix pecans, oats and flour on a sheet of waxed paper.
Stir sugar, butter and milk over low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nut mixture and vanilla; let cool 10 minutes.
Drop slightly rounded teaspoonful, 3 inches apart, on prepared cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes until cookies spread, look lacy and are lightly browned.
Cook on cookie sheets on wire rack 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until cookies harden slightly.
Remove from wire rack with broad metal spatula.

title: pea pickers cake
directions: Place these ingredients in bowl and mix with beater until oranges are completely mixed through mix.
Place in three 8-inch pans, well-greased.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, turn out cake to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into 1 quart casserole dish. Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: one dish microwave brownies
directions: In 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish, melt oleo and cocoa on stove.
Remove from heat and add sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, baking powder and nuts.
Microwave for 5 minutes, turning once halfway.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in water; add salt. When tender and thick, add scalded milk. Add beaten yolks, cream, sugar and raisins.
Turn into a buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with meringue made by beating the egg whites until stiff, then fold in the powdered sugar. Brown in a slow oven for about 12 minutes.

title: marshmallow krispies
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in double boiler.
Have marshmallows frozen individual on cookie sheet.
Dip marshmallows, one at a time in caramel mixture, then roll in Rice Krispies.
Set on waxed paper to harden.

title: chicken dijon(a favorite)
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken breasts in butter or margarine until tender, about 20 minutes. Remove chicken to warm serving platter.
Stir flour into skillet drippings.
Add chicken broth and light cream. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in mustard.
Add chicken. Cover and heat 10 minutes. Garnish with tomato and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate overnight.

title: grapes in cognac and sour cream
directions: Marinate grapes, marshmallows and pecans overnight in a mixture of the honey, lemon juice and Cognac.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In a saucepan over medium-high heat, cook shrimp, drain and add green onions, cucumber, pimientos, dill and cheese.
Whisk together lemon juice, olive oil, vinegar, mustard, garlic and pepper.
Pour over shrimp mixture and toss gently.

title: cranberry-pineapple bread
directions: Place all in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed until all is moistened, then at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Spread in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Last few minutes of baking, sprinkle with coconut or dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: mint delight
directions: Mix sprigs of mint with the tea and sugar.
Strain and cool in refrigerator.
Mix juice of lemon and orange with pineapple.
Add to grape juice and combine with tea base.
Add water.
Chill thoroughly and decorate before serving with fruit slices and remaining mint.

title: el paso cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a well-greased Bundt cake pan or large well greased iron skillet.
In a Bundt pan, bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.
In an iron skillet, bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.
Serves about 12.

title: biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, add rest of ingredients and mix until dough makes a ball.
Knead lightly until smooth.
Pinch off dough into little balls to make biscuits.
Place in iron skillet with a little oil in bottom, turn dough once to have oily side up.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
This dough will keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: egg, dried beef casserole
directions: Butter large 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover bottom with slightly over 1/2 bread cubes.
Add layer of dried beef, torn into bits, layer of grated cheese and repeat.
Beat eggs; add milk to eggs and pour over bread, beef, cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: old homestead skillet peach dumplings
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over butter. Lay in peach halves, sprinkled with 1 tablespoon of sugar.
Sift flour three times with baking powder, salt and 1 tablespoon sugar. Cut in shortening.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, bananas, dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix well and bake at 300° for 1 hour or until done.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Place peach halves, cut side down, in cooled pie crust. Empty instant pudding mix into deep bowl.
Add brown sugar, milk and sour cream.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed for two minutes.
Pour over peaches. Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Garnish with fresh peach slices.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, extract, baking powder and flour; mix well.
Beat the egg whites with electric mixer and add to cake mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: canned squash or okra
directions: Cover squash with water.
Add salt and cider vinegar.
Bring to a boil until it changes color.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: pig in blanket
directions: Put cabbage in hot water.
In another bowl, mix hamburger with onion.
Add rice.
Take leaves off cabbage and place small handful of hamburger mixture in cabbage and roll.
Place in skillet and add 2 (16 ounce) cans tomato sauce.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: pat's pizza breakfast
directions: Press rolls on pizza pan.
Brown and drain sausage; put on top of crust.
Put thawed hash browns on top of sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top of hash browns.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture evenly over top of pizza.
Cover top with Parmesan cheese.
Put in 375° oven.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Heats up well in microwave.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Place chilies on baking sheet and run under broiler to blister skin, turning several times to cook evenly.
Put in plastic bag for a few minutes until cool enough to peel.
Slit chilies and remove seeds.
Put 1/2 x 1/2-inch piece of cheese about 1-inch shorter than length of pepper in slit of pepper.
Roll in flour.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Beat yolks with water, 3 tablespoons flour and salt until thick and creamy.
Mix with egg whites.
Dip chilies in batter and fry in oil until coating is lightly browned.
Turn and brown opposite side.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with mixer until creamy.
Add shrimp. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Let refrigerate overnight.

title: russian salad
directions: Add lime jello to the 3/4 cup hot water. Heat over low heat. Add marshmallows and cream cheese. Heat until all melts or dissolves smooth. Set aside to cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in loaf pan and cover with strips of bacon.
Pour one 8 ounce can Hunt's tomato sauce over.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and spices.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut together the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg, vinegar and ice cold water.
Mix with your hands until smooth.
Divide mixture in half.
Roll out until large enough to go 1-inch over edge of pie plate.
Place in pie pan.
Add filling, if a top crust or lattice is to be added.
Roll out 2nd crust.
Place on top of filling.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Add rest of ingredients. Mix together and cook at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: velveeta cheese bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and put in crock-pot and let cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: meat ball sandwiches
directions: Mix together and brown.
Simmer in your favorite spaghetti sauce for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until done.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and mix well.
Add unchopped pecans.
Pour into large unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until firm.
This makes a large pie.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Crush wafers and add just enough melted butter to hold together.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Combine cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth. Whip the whipping cream until it makes soft peaks.
Fold into the cheese mixture.
Pour into the prepared crust.
Refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Top with your favorite fruit. Serve chilled.

title: skylar's chocolate bananas
directions: You also need 2 wooden sticks and mom's help.

title: jello salad
directions: Chill till partially frozen 1 can condensed milk.
In Pan bring to a rolling boil; 1 lg box Jello, 1 can crushed pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar.
Cool completely.
In mixing bowl cream 1 lg pkg. cream cheese until softened and add cooled jello and blend a few minutes. Chill till partially jelled.
Whip 1 can partially frozen condensed milk and fold in chilled jello mixture.
Place in large Pyrex or Tupperware container and cover with cool whip.
Top with crushed nuts and set in refrigerator.
Chill for a couple more hours or overnight.
Very Good.

title: toffee bar cake
directions: When cake is cooled completely, divide into 2 parts.
Crumble 1/2 cake into a very large bowl.
Layer 1/2 of pudding on cake, then layer 1/2 Cool Whip on pudding.
Sprinkle 1/2 Heath bar crumbs on Cool Whip.
Repeat layers, ending with Heath bar crumbs.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
